name: Pond Hut
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Basket Carrier
desc: Once each harvest, you can buy 1 <WOOD>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <GRAIN> for 2 <FOOD> total.

name: Carpenter's Apprentice
desc: Wood rooms cost you 2 <WOOD> less. Your 3rd and 4th stable each cost you 1 <WOOD> less. Your 13th to 15th fence each cost you nothing.

name: Reed-Hatted Toad
desc: Add 5, 7, 9, 11, and 13 to the current round and place 1 <REED> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <REED>.

name: Upholstery
desc: Each time you build or play an improvement after this one, you can place 1 <REED> on this card, irretrievably, to get 1 bonus <SCORE>, up to the number of rooms in your house.

name: Shoreforester
desc: When you play this card and each time 1 <REED> is placed on an empty __Reed Bank__ accumulation space in the preparation phase, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Carpenter's Bench
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can use the taken wood (and only that) to build exactly 1 pasture. If you do, one of the fences is free.

name: Henpecked Husband
desc: Each time you take a __Build Rooms__ action with the second person you place, return the first person you placed home, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Cooking Hearth
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>      <PIG> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
<SHEEP> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <CATTLE> <ARROW> 4<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>

name: Moldboard Plow
desc: Place 2 field tiles on this card. Twice this game, when you use the __Farmland__ action space, you can also plow 1 field from this card.

name: Ceilings
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on the next 5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>. Remove the <WOOD> promised by this card from future round spaces the next time you renovate.

name: Work Certificate
desc: Each time after you use an action space, you can take 1 building resource from a building resource accumulation space with at least 4 building resources on it.

name: Wolf
desc: Pile (from bottom to top) 1 <CLAY>, 1 <WOOD>, and 1 <GRAIN> on this card. Each time you get a good matching the top item, you can move that item to your supply and get 1 <PIG>.

name: Stone Oven
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW-2X> 4<FOOD>
[When you build it, you can Bake immediatly]

name: Well
desc: [Put 1 <FOOD> on the 5 next turns. At the start of each turn, collect the <FOOD>]

name: Gift Basket
desc: When you play this card, if you have exactly 2/3/4/5 rooms, you immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>/<FOOD>/<GRAIN>/<VEGETABLE>.

name: Mud Patch
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <PIG>. You can hold 1 <PIG> on each of your unplanted field tiles.

name: Small-scale Farmer
desc: As long as you live in a house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each round, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Seasonal Worker
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get 1 additional <GRAIN>. From round 6 on, you can choose to get 1 <VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Shepherd's Crook
desc: Each time you fence a new pasture covering at least 4 farmyard spaces, you immediately get 2 sheep on this pasture.

name: Wall Builder
desc: Each time you build at least 1 room, you can place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Loom
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1/4/7 <SHEEP>, you get 1/2/3 <FOOD>. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for every 3 <SHEEP>.

name: Fireplace
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <PIG> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>
<SHEEP> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <CATTLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>

name: Grocer
desc: Pile the following goods on this card (<WOOD>, <GRAIN>, <REED>, <STONE>, <VEGETABLE>, <CLAY>, <REED>, <VEGETABLE>). At any time, you can buy the top good for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Clearing Spade
desc: At any time, you can move 1 crop from a planted field containing at least 2 crops to an empty field.

name: Loam Pit
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you also get 3 <CLAY>.

name: Basketmaker's Workshop
desc: [Harvest]
<REED> <ARROW-1X> 3<FOOD>
[Scoring]
2/4/5<REED> <ARROW-1X> 1/2/3<SCORE>

name: Joinery
desc: [Harvest]
<WOOD> <ARROW-1X> 2<FOOD>
[Scoring]
3/5/7<WOOD> <ARROW-1X> 1/2/3<SCORE>

name: Fireplace
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <PIG> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>
<SHEEP> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <CATTLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>

name: Wood Harvester
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <WOOD>/1 <FOOD> for each wood accumulation space with exactly 2 <WOOD>/at least 3 <WOOD>.

name: Barn Shed
desc: Each time another player (or, in a solo game, you) uses the __Forest__ accumulation space, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: New Market
desc: Each time you use an action space card on round spaces 8 to 11, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Sower
desc: Each time you build a major improvement, place 1 <REED> from the general supply on this card. At any time, you can move the <REED> to your supply or exchange it for a __Sow__ action.

name: Huntsman's Hat
desc: For each new <PIG> you get from the effect of an action space, you also get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Sheep Well
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of <SHEEP> you have. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Clay Oven
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW-1X> 5<FOOD>
[When you build it, you can Bake immediatly]

name: Mining Hammer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. Each time you renovate, you can also build a stable without paying <WOOD>.

name: Scullery
desc: At the start of each round, if you live in a wooden house, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Consultant
desc: When you play this card in a 1-/2-/3-/4- player game, you immediately get 2 <GRAIN>/3 <CLAY>/2 <REED>/2 <SHEEP>.

name: Cottager
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can also either build exactly 1 room or renovate your house. Either way, you have to pay the cost.

name: Handplow
desc: Add 5 to the current round and place 1 field tile on the corresponding round space. At the start of that round, you can plow the field.

name: Adoptive Parents
desc: For 1 <FOOD>, you can take an action with offspring in the same round you get it. If you do, the offspring does not count as "newborn".

name: Hard Porcelain
desc: At any time, you can exchange 2/3/4 <CLAY> for 1/2/3 <STONE>.

name: Paper Maker
desc: Immediately before playing each occupation after this one, you can pay 1 <WOOD> total to get 1 <FOOD> for each occupation you have in front of you.

name: Clay Hut Builder
desc: Once you no longer live in a wooden house, place 2 <CLAY> on each of the next 5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CLAY>.

name: Groom
desc: When you play this card, immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>.

name: Stone Tongs
desc: Each time you use a stone accumulation space, you get 1 additional <STONE>.

name: Caravan
desc: This card provides room for 1 person.

name: Milk Jug
desc: Each time any player (including you) uses the __Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you get 3 <FOOD>, and each other player gets 1 <FOOD>.

name: Roof Ballaster
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately pay 1 <FOOD> to get 1 <STONE> for each room you have.

name: Kindling Gatherer
desc: Each time you get <FOOD> from an action space, you get 1 additional <WOOD>.

name: Barrow Pusher
desc: For each new field tile you get, you also get 1 <CLAY> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Sowing Master
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Each time after you use the __Grain Utilization__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Grain Bag
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you get 1 additional <GRAIN> for each <BAKE>-improvement you have.

name: Cooking Hearth
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>      <PIG> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
<SHEEP> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <CATTLE> <ARROW> 4<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>

name: Tree Farm Joiner
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next 2 odd-numbered round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD> and, immediately afterward, a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Brewery Pond
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you also get 1 <GRAIN> and 1 <WOOD>.

name: Ale-Benches
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, you can pay exactly 1 <GRAIN> from your supply to get 1 bonus <SCORE>. If you do, each other player gets 1 <FOOD>.

name: Herring Pot
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Mushroom Collector
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can exchange 1 <WOOD> for 2 <FOOD>. If you do, place the <WOOD> on the accumulation space.

name: Stallwright
desc: After you play your 2nd, 3rd, 5th, and 7th occupation (including this one), you can build 1 stable at no cost.

name: Young Farmer
desc: Each time you use the __Major Improvement__ action space, you also get 1 <GRAIN> and, afterward, you can take a __Sow__ action.

name: Beer Stall
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, for each empty unfenced stable you have, you can exchange 1 <GRAIN> for 5 <FOOD>.

name: Corn Schnapps Distillery
desc: Once per round, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> to place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Plow Maker
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 additional field.

name: Wild Greens
desc: Each time you sow, you get 1 <FOOD> for every different type of good that you sow.

name: Slurry Spreader
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, each time you take the last <GRAIN>/<VEGETABLE> from a field, you also get 2 <FOOD>/1 <FOOD>.

name: Lumber Pile
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately return up to 3 <STABLE> from your farmyard board to your supply and get 3 <WOOD> for each.

name: Green Grocer
desc: At the start of each round, you can make exactly one of the following exchanges: 1 <CATTLE> <ARROW> 1 <VEGETABLE>; 1 <VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 1 <CATTLE>; 2 <SHEEP> <ARROW> 1 <VEGETABLE>; 1 <VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 2 <SHEEP>; 2 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <GRAIN>; 1 <GRAIN> <ARROW> 2 <FOOD>

name: Sleight of Hand
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately exchange up to 4 building resources for an equal number of other building resources.

name: Loppers
desc: Each time you build 1 or more fences, you can also use this card to exchange 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FENCE> in your supply for 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Twibil
desc: Each time after any player (including you) builds at least 1 wood room, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Lazy Sowman
desc: Each time you decline an unconditional __Sow__ action on your turn, you can immediately place another person on an action space of your choice (even if it is occupied).

name: Oriental Fireplace
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 4<FOOD>      <SHEEP> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
<CATTLE> <ARROW> 5<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>

name: Field Fences
desc: You can immediately take a __Build Fences__ action, during which you do not have to pay <WOOD> for fences that you build next to field tiles.

name: Assistant Tiller
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can also plow 1 field.

name: Heirloom
desc: (This card has no additional effect.)

name: Iron Hoe
desc: At the end of each work phase, if you occupy both the __Grain Seeds__ and __Vegetable Seeds__ action spaces, you can plow 1 field.

name: Wood Saw
desc: Each time all other players have more people than you, you can take a __Build Rooms__ action without placing a person.

name: Field Watchman
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can also plow 1 field.

name: Special Food
desc: The next time you take animals from an accumulation space and accommodate all of them on your farm, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each of these animals.

name: Winter Caretaker
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. At the end of each harvest, you can buy exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Wood Field
desc: You can plant <WOOD> on this card as though it were 2 fields, but it is considered 1 field. Sow and harvest <WOOD> on this card as you would <GRAIN>.

name: Straw-Thatched Roof
desc: You no longer need <REED> to renovate or build a room.

name: Barley Mill
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <FOOD> for each grain field that you harvest.

name: Foreign Aid
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 6 <FOOD>. You may no longer use the action spaces of rounds 12 to 14.

name: Stone Company
desc: Immediately after each time you use a __Quarry__ accumulation space, you get a __Major or Minor Improvement__ action during which you must spend at least 1 <STONE>.

name: Animal Tamer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get your choice of 1 <WOOD> or 1 <GRAIN>. Instead of just 1 animal total, you can keep any 1 animal in each room of your house.

name: Stable Yard
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD> for each completed round left to play. At any time, you can exchange 1 <SHEEP> plus 1 <PIG> for 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Christianity
desc: When you play this card, all other players get 1 <FOOD> each.

name: Bunk Beds
desc: Once you have 4 rooms, your house can hold 5 people.

name: Canal Boatman
desc: Each time you use __Fishing__ or __Reed Bank__, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to immediately place another person on this card. If you do, you get your choice of 3 <STONE> or 1 <GRAIN> plus 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Fishing Net
desc: Each time another player uses the __Fishing__ accumulation space, they must first pay you 1 <FOOD>. Then, in the returning home phase of that round, place 2 <FOOD> on __Fishing__.

name: Breed Registry
desc: During scoring, if you gained at most 2 <SHEEP> from sources other than breeding during the game and have not turned any sheep into food, you get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Mineral Feeder
desc: At the start of each round that does not end with a harvest, if you have at least 1 <SHEEP> in a pasture, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Reed Belt
desc: Place 1 <REED> on each of the remaining space for rounds 5, 8, 10, and 12. At the start of these rounds, you get the <REED>.

name: Crudit
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately buy exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>. At any time, you can discard 1 <VEGETABLE> on top of another <VEGETABLE> in a field to get 4 <FOOD>.

name: Garden Hoe
desc: Each time you take an unconditional __Sow__ action planting <VEGETABLE> in at least 1 field, you get 1 <CLAY> and 1 <STONE>.

name: Stable Cleaner
desc: At any time, you can take the __Build Stables__ action without placing a person. If you do, each stable costs you 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Farmyard Manure
desc: Each time you build 1 or more stables in one turn, you place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Pitchfork
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, if the __Farmland__ action space is occupied you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: New Purchase
desc: Before the start of each round that ends with a harvest, you can buy one of each of the following crops: 2 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <GRAIN>; 4 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <VEGETABLE>

name: Alchemists Lab
desc: This card is an action space for all. A player who uses it gets 1 building resource of each type they already have. If another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 <FOOD>.

name: Full Farmer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <CLAY>. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each pasture you have holding the maximum number of animals.

name: Angler
desc: Each time after you use the __Fishing__ Accumulation space while there are at most 2 <FOOD> on that space, you get a __Major or Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Clay Supply
desc: Place 1 <CLAY> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CLAY>.

name: Feed Fence
desc: For each new stable you build, you get 1 <FOOD> for your last one, get 3 <FOOD>. Each time you build stables, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <CLAY> instead of 2 <WOOD>.

name: Spice Trader
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, place 3 <VEGETABLE> on the space for round 11. At the start of that round, you get the <VEGETABLE>.

name: Renovation Company
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 3 <CLAY>. Immediately after, you can renovate without paying any building resources.
prerequisite: In Wooden House with Exactly 2 Rooms

name: Geologist
desc: Each time you use the __Forest__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you also get 1 <CLAY>. In games with 3 or more players, this also applies to the __Clay Pit__.

name: Priest
desc: When you play this card, if you live in a clay house with exactly 2 rooms, you immediately get 3 <CLAY>, 2 <REED> and 2 <STONE>.

name: Renovation Preparer
desc: For each new wood/clay room you build, you get 2 <CLAY>/2 <STONE>.

name: Barn Cats
desc: If you have 1/2/3/4 stables, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2/3/4/5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Small Trader
desc: Each time you take a __Major or Minor Improvement__ action to play an improvement from your hand, you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Swing Plow
desc: Place 4 field tiles on this card. Each time you use the __Farmland__ action space, you can also plow up to 2 fields from this card.

name: Recruitment
desc: From round 5 on, provided you have room in your house, each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action, you can take a __Family Growth__ action instead.
prerequisite: No People Left in the House

name: Ambition
desc: Each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action on an action space, you can build a major improvement instead of playing a minor one.

name: Muddy Puddles
desc: Pile (from bottom to top) 1 <PIG>, 1 <FOOD>, 1 <CATTLE>, 1 <FOOD>, and 1 <SHEEP> on this card. At any time, you can pay 1 <CLAY> to take the top good.

name: Wood Expert
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <WOOD>. Each improvement costs you up to 2 <WOOD> less, if you pay 1 <FOOD> instead.

name: Mole Plow
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can plow 1 additional field.

name: Sheep Rug
desc: You can use any __Wish for Children__ action space, even if it is occupied by another player's person.

name: Hook Knife
desc: Once this game, when you have 9/8/7/6/5/5 <SHEEP> on your farm in a 1-/2-/3-/4-/5-/6- player game, you immediately get 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Artichoke Field
desc: This card is a field. During the field phase of each harvest, if you harvest at least 1good from this card, you also get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Chief Forester
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you also get a __Sow__ action for exactly 1 field.

name: Wood Slide Hammer
desc: On your first renovation, if you have at least 5 wood rooms, you can renovate to stone directly and you get a discount of 2 <STONE> on the renovation cost.

name: District Manager
desc: At the end of each work phase, if you used both the __Forest__ and __Grove__ accumulation spaces, you get 5 <FOOD>.

name: Grassland Harrow
desc: Add 1 to the current round for each building resource in your supply and place 1 field on the corresponding round space. A the start of the round, you can plow the field.

name: Blueprint
desc: You can build the major improvements __Joinery__, __Pottery__, and __Basketmaker's Workshop__ even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action. They each cost you 1 <STONE> less.

name: Plow Driver
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Packaging Artist
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. Each time you get a __Minor Improvement__ action, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action instead.

name: Stockman
desc: When you build your 2nd/3rd/4th stable, you immediately get 1 <CATTLE>/<PIG>/<SHEEP>, even if built on the same turn (but not retroactively).

name: Profiteering
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can exchange 1 building resource for another building resource.

name: Handcart
desc: Before each work phase, you can take 1 building resource from at most one <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE> accumulation space containing at least 6/5/4/4 building resources of the same type.

name: Shifting Cultivator
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can also pay 3 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Throwing Axe
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space while there is at least 1 <PIG> on the __Pig Market__ accumulation space, you also get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Clay Puncher
desc: When you play this card and each time after you use a __Lessons__ action space or the __Clay Pit__ accumulation space, you get 1 <CLAY>.

name: Rolling Pin
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have more <CLAY> than <WOOD> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Fire Protection Pond
desc: Once you no longer live in a wooden house, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Milking Parlor
desc: When you play this card, if you have at least 1/3/4 <SHEEP>, you immediately get 2/3/4 <FOOD>. The same applies if you have at least 1/2/3 <CATTLE>.

name: Grain Depot
desc: If you paid <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<STONE> for this card, place 1 <GRAIN> on each of the next 2/3/4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Pig Breeder
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <PIG>. Your <PIG> breed at the end of round 12 (if there is room for the new <PIG>).

name: Vegetable Slicer
desc: Each time you upgrade a Fireplace to a Cooking Hearth, you immediately get 2 <WOOD> and 1 <VEGETABLE> (not retroactively).

name: Nail Basket
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can place 1<STONE> from your supply on that space (for the next visitor) to take a __Build Fences__ action.

name: Asparagus Gift
desc: Each time you build a number of fences equal to or greater than the current round, you immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Pioneering Spirit
desc: This card is an action space for you only. In rounds 3-5, it provides a __Renovation__ action. In rounds 6-8, it provides your choice of 1 <VEGETABLE>, <PIG>, or <CATTLE>.

name: Home Brewer
desc: After the field phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <GRAIN> into your choice of 3 <FOOD> or 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Stockyard
desc: This card can hold up to 3 animals of the same type. (It is not considered a pasture).

name: Stable Architect
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each unfenced stable in your farmyard.

name: Lumber Mill
desc: Every improvement costs you 1 <WOOD> less.

name: Greengrocer
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Hedge Keeper
desc: Each time you take a __Build Fences__ action, you do not have to pay <WOOD> for 3 of the fences you build.

name: Manger
desc: During scoring, if your pastures cover at least 6/7/8/10 farm yard spaces, you get 1/2/3/4 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Corn Scoop
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you get 1 additional <GRAIN>.

name: Kettle
desc: At any time, you can exchange 1/3/5 <GRAIN> for 3/4/5 <FOOD> and 0/1/2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Reap Hook
desc: Place 1 <GRAIN> on each of the next 3 of the round spaces 4, 7, 9, 11, 13, and 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Gritter
desc: At the end of each action in which you sow vegetables in a field, you get 1 <FOOD> for each vegetable field you have (including the new ones).

name: Layabout
desc: When you play this card, you must skip the next harvest. (You also do not have to feed your family that harvest.)

name: Bucksaw
desc: Each time you renovate, you can also pay 1 <WOOD> to get 1 bonus <SCORE> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Storehouse Keeper
desc: Each time you use the __Resource Market__ action space, you also get your choice of 1 <CLAY> or 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Acorns Basket
desc: Place 1 <PIG> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <PIG>.

name: Conservator
desc: You can renovate your wooden house directly to stone without renovating it to clay first.

name: Animal Dealer
desc: Each time you use the __Sheep Market__, __Pig Market__, or __Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you can buy 1 additional animal of the respective type for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Chimney Sweep
desc: Renovating to stone costs you 2 <STONE> less. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each other player living in a stone house.

name: Fodder Chamber
desc: During scoring in a game with 1/2/3/4+ players, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for every 7th/5th/4th/3rd animal on your farm.

name: Hide Farmer
desc: During scoring, you can pay 1 <FOOD> each for any number of unused farmyard spaces. You do not lose points for these spaces.

name: Nave
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each of the 5 columns of your farmyard board containing at least one room.

name: Seed Trader
desc: Place 2 <GRAIN> and 2 <VEGETABLE> on this card. You can buy them at any time. Each <GRAIN> costs 2 <FOOD>; each <VEGETABLE> costs 3 <FOOD>.

name: Pig Owner
desc: The first time after you play this card that you have 5 <PIG> on your farm, you immediately get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Village Peasant
desc: At the start of scoring, you get a number of <VEGETABLE> equal to the smallest of the numbers of major improvements, minor improvements, and occupations you have.

name: Stone Carver
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <STONE> into 3 <FOOD>.

name: Cherry Orchard
desc: This card is a field on which you can only sow and harvest wood as you would grain. Each time you harvest the last <WOOD> from this card, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Organic Farmer
desc: During the scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each pasture containing at least 1 animal while having unused capacity for at least three more animals.

name: Sleeping Corner
desc: You can use any __Wish for Children__ action space even if it is occupied by one other player's person.

name: Stone House Reconstruction
desc: At any time, you can renovate your clay house to a stone house without placing a person. (You must pay the normal renovation cost.)

name: Small Basket
desc: Each time after you use the __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you can pay 1 <REED> to get 1 <VEGETABLE>. If you do in a game with 4+ players, place that 1 <REED> on the accumulation space.

name: Cow Prince
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each space in your farmyard (including rooms) holding at least 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Pottery
desc: [Harvest]
<CLAY> <ARROW-1X> 2<FOOD>
[Scoring]
3/5/7<CLAY> <ARROW-1X> 1/2/3<SCORE>

name: Building Expert
desc: Each time you use the __Resource Market__ action space with the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th person you place, you also get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE>/<STONE>.

name: Champion Breeder
desc: Each time you place 2 or 3+ newborn animals on your farm during the breeding phase of the harvest, you get 1 or 2 bonus <SCORE>, respectively.

name: Carpenter's Yard
desc: You can build the __Joinery__ and __Well__ major improvement even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action, or you can build both with a single __Major Improvement__ action.

name: Hammer Crusher
desc: Immediately before you renovate to stone, you get 2 <CLAY> and 1 <REED> and you can take a __Build Rooms__ action.

name: Writing Desk
desc: Each time you use a __Lessons__ action space, you can play 1 additional occupation for an occupation cost of 2 <FOOD>.

name: Resource Hoarder
desc: Pile resources as depicted on this card. You can use the top item(s) when building a room, playing/building an improvement, or renovating. (From bottom to top: <STONE>, <CLAY>, <STONE>, <REED>, <WOOD>, <CLAY>)

name: Wood Cutter
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 1 additional <WOOD>.

name: Milking Stool
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1/3/5 <CATTLE>, you get 1/2/3 <FOOD>. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for every 2 <CATTLE> you have.

name: Delayed Wayfarer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 building resource of your choice and, once all people have been placed this round, you can place a person from your supply.

name: Knapper
desc: Each time before you use an action space card on round spaces 5 to 7, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Iron Oven
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW-1X> 6<FOOD>
When you play this card, you can immediately take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Turnwrest Plow
desc: Place 2 field tiles on this card. Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can also plow up to 2 fields from this card.

name: Frame Builder
desc: Each time you build a room/renovate, but only once per room/action, you can replace exactly 2 <CLAY> or 2 <STONE> with 1 <WOOD>.

name: Hunting Trophy
desc: Improvements built on __House Redevelopment__ cost you 1 building resource of your choice less. Fences built on __Farm Redevelopment__ cost you a total of 3 <WOOD> less.

name: Grange
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>.
prerequisite: 6 Field Tiles and All Animal Types

name: Clay Kneader
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 2 <CLAY>. Each time after you use __Grain Seeds__ or __Vegetable Seeds__ action space, you get 1 <CLAY>.

name: Gypsy's Crock
desc: Each time you use a cooking improvement to turn 2 goods into <FOOD> at the same time, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Estate Worker
desc: Place 1 <WOOD>, 1 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <STONE> in this order on the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective building resource.

name: Shaving Horse
desc: Each time after you obtain at least 1 <WOOD>, if you then have 5 or more <WOOD> in your supply, you can exchange 1 <WOOD> for 3 <FOOD>. With 7 or more <WOOD>, you must do so.

name: Stew
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, also place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Farmstead
desc: After each turn in which you make at least one unused farmyard space used, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Rock Garden
desc: You can only plant <STONE> on this card. Plant as though it were 3 fields, but it is considered 1 field. Sow and harvest <STONE> on this card as you would vegetables.

name: Pen Builder
desc: At any time, you can discard 1 <WOOD> from your supply. This card can hold two animals of any type for each <WOOD> discarded this way.

name: Seed Almanac
desc: Each time after you play a minor improvement after this one, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Fir Cutter
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. Each time after you use an animal accumulation space with your 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th person, you get 1/1/2/2/3 <WOOD>.

name: Seed Servant
desc: Each time after you use the __Grain Seeds__ or __Vegetable Seeds__ action space, you can take a __Bake bread__ or __Sow__ action, respectively.

name: Water Gully
desc: Place 1 <CATTLE>, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <CATTLE> on the next 3 round spaces (in that order). At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Bottles
desc: For each person you have, you must pay an additional 1 <CLAY> and 1 <FOOD> to play this card.

name: Claypipe
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you gained at least 7 building resources in the preceding work phase, you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Bread Paddle
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. For each occupation you play, you get an additional __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Rammed Clay
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <CLAY>. You can use <CLAY> instead of <WOOD> to build fences.

name: Dutch Windmill
desc: Each time you take a __Bake Bread__ action in a round immediately following a harvest, you get 3 additional <FOOD>.

name: Legworker
desc: Each time you use an action space that is orthogonally adjacent to another action space occupied by one of your people, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Dentist
desc: At the start of each harvest, you can place 1 <WOOD> from your supply on this card, irretrievably. In each feeding phase, you get 1 <FOOD> for each <WOOD> on this card.

name: Mineralogist
desc: Each time you use a clay/stone accumulation space, you also get 1 of the other good, <STONE>/<CLAY>.

name: Drill Harrow
desc: Each time before you take an unconditional __Sow__ action, you can pay 3 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Tea House
desc: Once per round, you can skip placing your second person and get 1 <FOOD> instead. (You can place the person later that round.)

name: Hand Truck
desc: Each time before you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you also get 1 <GRAIN> for each of your people occupying an accumulation space.

name: Carrot Museum
desc: At the end of rounds 8, 10, and 12, you get 1 <STONE> for each vegetable field you have and a number of <WOOD> equal to the number of <VEGETABLE> in your supply.

name: Confidant
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> from your supply on each of the next 2, 3, or 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD> back and your choice of a __Sow__ or __Build Fences__ action.

name: Almsbag
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN> for every 2 completed rounds.

name: Plow Hero
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space with the first person you place in a round, you can plow 1 additional field for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Dung Collector
desc: Each time you get 2 or more newborn animals, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Skillful Renovator
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <CLAY>. Each time after you renovate, you get a number of <WOOD> equal to the number of people you placed that round.

name: Cookery Extension
desc: Each harvest, you can use each of your cooking improvements once to get double the amount of <FOOD> for 1 animal or <VEGETABLE>.

name: Forest Owner
desc: This card is an action space for all. If another player uses it, they get 3 <WOOD> and must give you 1 <WOOD> from the general supply. If you use it, you get 4 <WOOD>.

name: Cattle Buyer
desc: Each time another player uses the __Fencing__ action space, you can buy exactly 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> from the general supply for 1/2/2 <FOOD>.

name: Credit
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 5 <FOOD>. At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you must pay 1 <FOOD>, or else take a <BEGGING> marker.

name: Material Deliveryman
desc: Each time any player (including you) takes 5/6/7/8+ goods from an accumulation space, you get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE> from the general supply.

name: Farm Hand
desc: Once this game, if you have 4 field tiles in a 2x2, you can build a stable in the center of the 2x2 during a __Build Stables__ action. This stable provides room for a person but not animals.

name: Apiary
desc: At the end of each work phase, you can sow exactly 1 crop on 1 field.

name: Rocky Terrain
desc: Each time you plow a field (tile or card), you can also buy 1 <STONE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Reseller
desc: Once this game, immediately after playing or building an improvement, you can choose to get its printed cost from the general supply.

name: Livestock Feeder
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. This card can hold 1 animal of any type for each <GRAIN> in your supply.

name: Forest School
desc: You can consider the __Lessons__ action spaces not occupied. You can replace each <FOOD> that an occupation costs with <WOOD>.

name: Sheep Agent
desc: You can keep 1 <SHEEP> on this card for each occupation card in front of you (including this one), unless it is already able to hold animals.

name: Chophouse
desc: Each time you use the __Grain/Vegetable Seeds__ action space, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3/2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Truffle Searcher
desc: This card can hold a number of <PIG> equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Agrarian Fences
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Utilization__ action space, you can take a __Build Fences__ action instead of one of the two actions provide by the action space.

name: Large-Scale Farmer
desc: Each time after you use the __Farm Expansion__ or __Major Improvement__ action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to use that other space with the same person.

name: Dolly's Mother
desc: You only require 1 <SHEEP> to breed sheep during the breeding phase of a harvest. This card can hold 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Wood Workshop
desc: Each time before you play or build an improvement, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Pet Broker
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <SHEEP>. You can keep 1 <SHEEP> on this card for each occupation in front of you.

name: Museum Caretaker
desc: At the start of each work phase, if you have at least 1 <WOOD>, 1 <CLAY>, 1<REED>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <VEGETABLE> in your supply, you get 1bonus <SCORE>.

name: Homekeeper
desc: Exactly one clay or stone room in your house can hold an additional person if the room is adjacent to both a field and a pasture.

name: Seed Pellets
desc: Each time before you take an unconditional __Sow__ action, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Pattern Maker
desc: Each time another player renovates, you can exchange exactly 2 <WOOD> for 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <FOOD>, and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Herbal Garden
desc: From now on, at least one of your pastures must contain no animals.

name: Reader
desc: As soon as you have 6 (__7 in draft mode__) occupations in front of you (including this one), this cards provides room for one person.

name: Lettuce Patch
desc: This card is a field that can only grow vegetables. You can immediately turn each <VEGETABLE> you harvested from this card into 4 <FOOD>.

name: Cow Patty
desc: Each time you sow in a field that is orthogonally adjacent to a pasture, you can place 1 additional good of the planted type in it.

name: Land Register
desc: During scoring, if your farm has no unused spaces, you get 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Cattle Farm
desc: For each pasture you have, you can keep 1 <CATTLE> on this card.

name: Churchyard
desc: Place 2 <FOOD> on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>. (*Occupations and Improvements)

name: Basket Weaver
desc: When you play this card, immediately build the __Basketmaker's Workshop__ major improvement for 1 <STONE> and 1 <REED>.

name: Sundial
desc: At the end of the work phases of rounds 7 and 9, you can take a __Sow__ action without placing a person.

name: Roof Examiner
desc: When you play this card, if you have 1/2/3/4 major improvements, you immediately get 2/3/4/5 <REED>.

name: Sheep Walker
desc: At any time, you can exchange 1 <SHEEP> on your farmyard for either 1 <PIG>, 1 <VEGETABLE>, or 1 <STONE>.

name: Potato Ridger
desc: Each time after you harvest 1+ <VEGETABLE>, if you then have 3+ <VEGETABLE> in your supply, you can turn exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> into 6 <FOOD>. With 4+ <VEGETABLE>, you must do so.

name: Digging Spade
desc: Each time you use a clay accumulation space, you also get a number of <FOOD> equal to the number of <PIG> in your farmyard.

name: Delivery Nurse
desc: Once this game, if you have all types of animals, you can use any __Wish for Children__ action space even without room.

name: Culinary Artist
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can exchange your choice of 1 <GRAIN>/<SHEEP>/<VEGETABLE> for 4/5/7 <FOOD>.

name: Straw Manure
desc: Before the field phase of each harvest, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> from your supply to add 1 <VEGETABLE> to each of up to 2 vegetable fields.

name: Party Organizer
desc: As soon as the next player but you gains their 5th person, you immediately get 8 <FOOD> (not retroactively). During scoring, if only you have 5 people, you get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Hardware Store
desc: Each time after you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can pay 2 <FOOD> total to buy 1 <WOOD>, 1 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <STONE>.

name: Stablehand
desc: Each time you build at least 1 fence, you can also build a stable without paying <WOOD> for the stable.

name: Animal Driver
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have 1/2/3+ fenced stables, you get 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE>.

name: Cheese Fondue
desc: Each time you bake at least 1 <GRAIN> into bread, you get 1 additional <FOOD> if you have at least 1<SHEEP> and (another) 1 additional <FOOD> if you have at least 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Constable
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with no negative points in any scoring line gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Hoof Caregiver
desc: Immediately add 1 <CATTLE> from the general supply to the __Cattle Market__ accumulation space. Afterward, for each cattle on __Cattle Market__, you get 1 <GRAIN> plus 1 <FOOD>.

name: Swimming Class
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you return a person from the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get 2 bonus <SCORE> for each newborn that you return home.

name: Garden Designer
desc: At the start of scoring, you can place <FOOD> in empty fields. You get 1/2/3 bonus <SCORE> for each field in which you place 1/4/7 <FOOD>.

name: Storeroom
desc: During scoring, you get  bonus <SCORE> for each pair of <GRAIN> plus <VEGETABLE> you have (considering all crops in your supply and fields), rounded up.

name: Cowherd
desc: Each time you use the __Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you get 1 additional <CATTLE>.

name: Ox Goad
desc: Each time after you use the __Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you can pay 2 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Lynchet
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <FOOD> for each harvested field tile that is orthogonally adjacent to your house.

name: Newly-Plowed Field
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately plow 1 field, which needs not be adjacent to another field.

name: Lover
desc: When you play this card, immediately pay an amount of <FOOD> equal to the number of complete rounds left to play to take a __Family Growth Even without Room__ action.

name: Master Huntsman
desc: When you play this card and each time you build a major improvement, you get 1 <PIG>.

name: Cattle Feeder
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can also buy 1 <CATTLE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Sculpture Course
desc: At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can use this card to exchange your choice of 1 <WOOD> for 2 <FOOD>, or 1 <STONE> for 4 <FOOD>.

name: Task Artisan
desc: When you play this card and each time a stone accumulation space appears on a round space in the preparation phase, you get 1 <WOOD> and a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Forest Stone
desc: Place 2 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you use a wood accumulation space, move 1 of these <FOOD> to your supply. Each time you use a stone accumulation space, add 2 <FOOD> to this card.

name: Trimmer
desc: In each work phase, after you enclose at least one farmyard space, you get 2 <STONE>. (Subdividing an existing pasture does not count.)

name: Omnifarmer
desc: Each harvest, you can place 1 harvested crop or 1 newborn animal on this card, irretrievably. Once this game, if there are 2/3/4/5 different goods on this, you get 3/5/7/9 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Soldier
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each <STONE> + <WOOD> pair in your supply. You cannot score additional points for the resources scored with this card.

name: Scythe Worker
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. In the field phase of each harvest, you can harvest 1 additional <GRAIN> from each of your grain fields.

name: Lutenist
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 <WOOD>. Immediately after, you can buy exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Emissary
desc: At any time, you can place a good from your supply on this card to get 1 <STONE>. You must place different goods on this card. (<FOOD> is also considered a good.)

name: Field Cultivator
desc: Pile 1 <WOOD>, 1 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <REED>, 1 <CLAY>, and 1 <WOOD> on this card. Each time you harvest a field tile, you can also take the top good from the pile.

name: Steam Machine
desc: Each work phase, if the last action space you use is an accumulation space, you can immediately afterward take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Reclamation Plow
desc: After the next time you take animals from an accumulation space and accommodate all of them on your farm, you can plow 1 field.

name: Boar Spear
desc: Each time you get at least 1 <PIG> outside of the breeding phase of a harvest, you can immediately turn them into 4 <FOOD> each.

name: Stone Buyer
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately buy exactly 2 <STONE> for 1 <FOOD>. From the next round on, once per round, you can buy 1 <STONE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Mayor Candidate
desc: You immediately get 2 <WOOD> and 2 <STONE>. During scoring, you get 1 negative point for each <WOOD> and each <STONE> in your supply. You can no longer discard <WOOD> or <STONE>.

name: Stone Axe
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can return 1 <STONE> to the general supply to get an additional 3 <WOOD>.

name: Scythe
desc: During the field phase of each harvest, you can select exactly one of your fields and harvest all the crops planted in it.

name: Millwright
desc: You immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. Each time you build fences, stables, and rooms, or renovate your house, you can replace up to 2 building resources of any type with 1 <GRAIN> each.

name: Double-Turn Plow
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately plow up to 2 fields.

name: Junk Room
desc: Each time after you build an improvement, including this one, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Rod Collection
desc: Each time you use __Fishing__, you can place up to 2 <WOOD> on this card, irretrievably. During scoring, each such <WOOD> is worth 1 bonus <SCORE>, except the 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th.

name: Basketmaker's Wife
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <REED> and 1 <FOOD>. At any time, you can turn 1 <REED> into 2 <FOOD>.

name: Land Consolidation
desc: UPDATED: At any time, if you have a grain field with exactly 3 sown <GRAIN>, you can exchange the <GRAIN> on the field for 1 <VEGETABLE> on the field.

name: Melon Patch
desc: This card is a field that can only grow vegetables. Each time you harvest the last <VEGETABLE> from this card, you can plow 1 field.

name: Retraining
desc: At the end of each turn in which you renovate, you can exchange your __Joinery__ for the __Pottery__ or your __Pottery__ for the __Basketmaker's Workshop__.

name: Lasso
desc: You can place exactly two people immediately after one another if at least one of them uses the __Sheep Market__, __Pig Market__, or __Cattle Market__ accumulation space.

name: Sheep Provider
desc: Each time any player (including you) uses the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Ash Trees
desc: When you play this card, immediately place (up to) 5 fences from your supply on it. When you build fences, fences taken from this card cost you nothing.

name: Club House
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces and 1 <STONE> on the round space after that. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Bean Counter
desc: Each time you use an action space on round spaces 1 to 8, place 1 <FOOD> on this card. Each time this cards has 3 <FOOD> on it, move the <FOOD> to your supply.

name: Material Hub
desc: Immediately place 2 of each building resource on this card. Each time any player (including you) takes at least 5 <WOOD>, 4 <CLAY>, 3 <REED>, or 3 <STONE>, you get 1 of that building resource from this card.
prerequisite: 1 reed and 1 stone in your supply

name: Wood Barterer
desc: Each time before you use an action space with a __Build Fences__ or __Build Rooms__ action, you can choose to either get 2 <WOOD> or exchange up to 2 <WOOD> for 1 <REED> each.

name: Brewing Water
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> to place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Education Bonus
desc: After you play your 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th occupation this game, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE>/<VEGETABLE>/<FIELD> (not retroactively).

name: Cob
desc: At the start of each work phase, if you have at least 1 <CLAY> in your supply, you can exchange exactly 1 <GRAIN> for 2 <CLAY> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Trout Pool
desc: At the start of each work phase, if there are at least 3 <FOOD> on the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get 1 <FOOD> from the general supply.

name: Cube Cutter
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. In the field phase of each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD> for 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Skimmer Plow
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__  action space, you can plow 2 fields instead of 1. Each time you sow, you must place 1 fewer good on each field you sow.

name: Milking Place
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you get 1 <FOOD>. You can no longer hold animals in your house (not even via another card).

name: Potter Ceramics
desc: Each time before you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you can exchange 1 <CLAY> for 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Trowel
desc: At any time, you can renovate your house to stone. From a wooden house, this costs 1 <STONE>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <FOOD> per room. From a clay house, this costs 1 <STONE> per room.

name: Corf
desc: Each time any player (including you) takes at least 3 <STONE> from an accumulation space, you get 1 <STONE> from the general supply.

name: Roughcaster
desc: Each time you build at least 1 clay room or renovate your house from clay to stone, you also get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Pellet Press
desc: Once per round, you can pay 1 <REED>. If you do, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Baking Course
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>
At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Roof Ladder
desc: Each time you renovate, you pay 1 fewer <REED> and, at the end of the action, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Porter
desc: Each time you take at least 4 of the same building resource from an accumulation space, you get 1 additional building resource of the accumulating type and 1 <FOOD>

name: Ebonist
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <WOOD> into 1 <FOOD> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Resource Recycler
desc: Each time another player renovates to stone, if you live in a clay house, you can pay 2 <FOOD> to build a clay room at no additional cost.

name: Sample Stable Maker
desc: At the start of each returning home phase, you can return a built stable to your supply to get 1 <WOOD>, 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <FOOD>, and a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Open Air Farmer
desc: When you play this card, you remove exactly 3 <STABLE> in your supply from play to build a pasture covering 2 farmyard spaces. You only need to pay a total of 2 <WOOD> for fences

name: Trellis
desc: Each time before you use the __Pig Market__ accumulation space, you can take a __Build Fences__ action. (You must pay <WOOD> for the fences as usual.)

name: Beanfield
desc: This card is a field that can only grow vegetables.

name: Grain Thief
desc: Each time you would harvest a grain field, you can leave the grain on the field and take 1 <GRAIN> from the general supply instead.

name: Winnowing Fan
desc: After the field phase of each harvest, you can use a <BAKE>-improvement but only to turn exactly 1 <GRAIN> into <FOOD>. (This is not considered a __Bake Bread__ action.)

name: Trade Teacher
desc: Each time after you use a __Lesson__ action space, you can buy up to 2 different goods: <GRAIN>, <STONE>, <SHEEP>, and <PIG> for 1 <FOOD> each; <CATTLE> and <VEGETABLE> for 2 food each.

name: Crop Rotation Field
desc: This card is a field. Each time you remove the last <GRAIN> or <VEGETABLE> from this card, you can immediately sow <VEGETABLE> or <GRAIN> on this card, respectively.

name: Artisan District
desc: During scoring, you get 2/5/8 bonus <SCORE> for having 3/4/5 major improvements from the bottom row of the supply board.

name: Fatstock Stretcher
desc: Each time you turn a <SHEEP> or <PIG> into <FOOD> using a cooking improvement, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Timber Shingle Maker
desc: When you renovate to stone, you can place up to 1 <WOOD> from your supply in each of your rooms. During scoring, each such <WOOD> is worth 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Town Hall
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, if you live in a clay or stone house, you get 1 or 2 <FOOD>, respectively.

name: Potter's Yard
desc: Immediately place 1 <CLAY> on each unused space in your farmyard. Each time you turn a space into a used space, you get the clay and you can immediately exchange it for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Braggart
desc: During the scoring, you get 2/3/4/5/7/9 bonus <SCORE> for having at least 5/6/7/8/9/10 improvements in front of you.

name: Pet Grower
desc: Each time you use an animal accumulation space, if afterward you have no animal in your house, you also get 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Housebook Master
desc: After playing this card, if you renovate to stone in round 13/12/11 or before, you immediately get 1/2/3 <FOOD> and 1/2/3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Wildlife Reserve
desc: This card can hold up to 1 <SHEEP>, 1 <PIG>, and 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Chicken Coop
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 8 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Uncaring Parents
desc: At the end of each harvest, if you live in a stone house, you get 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Dairy Crier
desc: When you play this card, each player (including you) can choose to get 2 <SHEEP> or 2 <FOOD>; you also get 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Fellow Grazer
desc: During scoring, you get 2 bonus <SCORE> for each pasture you have covering at least 3 farmyard spaces.

name: Feeding Dish
desc: Each time you use an animal accumulation space while already having an animal of that type, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Value Assets
desc: After each harvest, you can buy exactly one of the following goods: 1 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <WOOD>; 1 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <CLAY>; 2 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <REED>; 2 <FOOD> <ARROW> 1 <STONE>

name: Clay Firer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <CLAY>. At any time, you can turn <CLAY> into <STONE>: you get 1 <STONE> for 2 <CLAY>, and 2 <STONE> for 3 <CLAY>.

name: Wooden Hut Extender
desc: Wood rooms now cost you 1 <REED>, and additionally 5 <WOOD> through round 5, 4 <WOOD>  in rounds 6 and 7, and 3 <WOOD>  in round 8 and later.

name: Forest Well
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining round space, up to the amount of <WOOD> in your supply. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Smuggler
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange up to 2 goods as follows:
[<WOOD> <ARROW> <GRAIN>]
or
[<GRAIN> <ARROW> <STONE>]

name: Den Builder
desc: When you live in a clay or stone house, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> and 2 <FOOD>. If you do, for the rest of the game, this card provides room for exactly one person.

name: Roll-Over Plow
desc: At any time, if you have at least 3 planted fields, you can discard all goods from one of those fields to plow 1 field.

name: Social Benefits
desc: Immediately after the feeding phase of each harvest, if you have no <FOOD> left, you get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <CLAY>.

name: Brick Hammer
desc: Each time after you build an improvement costing at least 2 <CLAY>, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Farm Building
desc: Each time you build a major improvement, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Collector
desc: This card is an action space for you only. When you use it for the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th time, you get 1 <BEGGING> marker and 6/7/8/9 different good of your choice.

name: Feed Pellets
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <SHEEP>. In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> for 1 animal of a type you already have.

name: Master Workman
desc: Each time before you use an action space card on round spaces 1/2/3/4, you get 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED>/<STONE>.

name: Carpenter's Hammer
desc: Each time you build at least 2 wood/clay/stone rooms at once, you get a total discount of 2 <REED> as well as 2 <WOOD>/3 <CLAY>/4 <STONE>.

name: Roman Pot
desc: Place 4 <FOOD> from the general supply on this card. At the start of each work phase, if you are the last player in turn order, move 1 <FOOD> from this card to your supply.

name: Furnisher
desc: UPDATED: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <WOOD>. Each time after you build at least one new room, you can build or play a number of improvements equal to the number of new rooms you built, paying up to 1 <WOOD> less for each such improvement.

name: Imitator
desc: If you have a person on the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can use non-accumulating round 1-9 action spaces even if they are occupied.

name: Roastmaster
desc: Each time you use the __Traveling Players__ or __Fishing__ accumulation spaces, you can move exactly 1 <FOOD> from that space to the other to get 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Child Ombudsman
desc: From round 5 on, if you have room in your house, at the end of each person action, you can take a __Family Growth__ action with that person. If you do, you get 2 negative <SCORE>.

name: Fish Farmer
desc: Each time there is 1/2/3+ food on the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get an additional 2 <FOOD> on the __Reed Bank__/ __Clay Pit__/ __Forest__ accumulation spaces.

name: Plowman
desc: Add 4, 7, and 10 to the current round and place a field tile on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you can plow the field for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Working Gloves
desc: When you play this card, you get 1 <FOOD>. Each time you pay an occupation cost, you can pay 1 building resource of your choice in place of (up to) 2 <FOOD>.

name: Work Permit
desc: Add 1 to the current round for each building resource you have and place 1 person from your supply on the corresponding round space. In that round, you can use the person.

name: Feedyard
desc: This card can hold 1 animal for each pasture you have, even different types. After the breeding phase of each harvest, you get 1 <FOOD> for each unused spot on this card.

name: Tutor
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each occupation played after this one.

name: Brook
desc: Each time you use one of the four action spaces above the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Three-Field Rotation
desc: At the start of the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1 <GRAIN> field, 1 <VEGETABLE> field, and 1 empty field, you get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Firewood Collector
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__, __Grain Seeds__, __Grain Utilization__, or __Cultivation__ action space, at the end of that turn, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Master Bricklayer
desc: Each time you build a major improvement, reduce the <STONE> cost by the number of rooms you have built onto your initial house.

name: Bee Statue
desc: Pile (from bottom to top) 1 <VEGETABLE>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN> on this card. Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get the top good.

name: Established Person
desc: If your house has exactly 2 rooms, immediately renovate it without paying any building resources. If you do, you can immediately afterward take a __Build Fences__ action.

name: Clay Carrier
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <CLAY>. At any time, but only once per round, you can buy 2 <CLAY> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Pioneer
desc: When you play this card and each time before you use the most recent action space card, you get 1 building resource of your choice and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Silokeeper
desc: Each time you use the action space card that has been revealed right before the most recent harvest, you also get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Blighter
desc: When you play this card, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each complete stage left to play. You may not play any more occupations.

name: Field Spade
desc: Each time after you sow in at least 1 field, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Bed Maker
desc: Each time you add rooms to your house, you can also pay 1 <WOOD> and 1 <GRAIN> to immediately get a __Family Growth with Room Only__ action.

name: Carpenter
desc: Every new room only costs you 3 of the appropriate building resource and 2 <REED> (e.g. if you live in a wooden house, 3 <WOOD> and 2 <REED>).

name: Stock Protector
desc: Each time before you use the __Fencing__ action space, you get 2 <WOOD>. Immediately after that __Fencing__ action, you can place another person.

name: Earth Oven
desc: [Anytime]
<VEGETABLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>      <PIG> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
<SHEEP> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>      <CATTLE> <ARROW> 3<FOOD>
[__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>

name: Master Renovator
desc: At the end of the work phases of rounds 7 and 9, you can take a __Renovation__ action without placing a person and pay 1 building resource of your choice less.

name: Muck Rake
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for exactly 1 unfenced stable holding exactly 1 <SHEEP>. The same applies to <PIG> and <CATTLE>, if held in different unfenced stables.

name: Recycled Brick
desc: Each time any player (including you) renovates to stone, you get 1 <CLAY> for each newly renovated room.

name: Baker
desc: When you play this card and at the start of each feeding phase, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Thick Forest
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Carpenter's Parlor
desc: Wooden rooms only cost you 2 <WOOD> and 2 <REED> each.

name: Whisky Distiller
desc: At any time, you can pay 1 <GRAIN>. If you do, add 2 to the current round and place 4 <FOOD> on the corresponding round space. At the start of that round, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Bookcase
desc: Each time after you play an occupation, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Petting Zoo
desc: As long as you have a pasture orthogonally adjacent to your house, you can keep animals of any type on this card, up to the number of rooms in your house.

name: Lord of the Manor
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each scoring category in which you score the maximum 4 points. (The bonus point is also awarded for 4 fenced stables.)

name: Wooden Whey Bucket
desc: Each time before you use the __Sheep Market__/__Cattle Market__ accumulation space, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>/at no cost.

name: Pigswill
desc: Each time you use the __Fencing__ action space, you also get 1 <PIG>.

name: Eternal Rye Cultivation
desc: After each harvest in which you have 2 or 3+ <GRAIN> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 additional <GRAIN>, respectively.

name: Lawn Fertilizer
desc: Your pastures of size 1 can hold up to 3 animals of the same type. (With a stable, they can hold up to 6 animals of the same type.)

name: Nutrition Expert
desc: At the start of each round, you can exchange a set comprised of 1 animal of any type, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <VEGETABLE> for 5 <FOOD> and 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Child's Toy
desc: During the feeding phase of each harvest, your newborns require 2 <FOOD> (instead of 1).

name: Godmother
desc: Each time you take a __Family Growth__ action, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Stone Weir
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, if there are 0/1/2/3 <FOOD> on the space, you get an additional 4/3/2/1 <FOOD> from the general supply.

name: Strawberry Patch
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Muddy Waters
desc: Alternate placing 1 <FOOD> and 1 <CLAY> on each remaining even-numbered round space, starting with <FOOD>. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Bricklayer
desc: Each improvement and each renovation cost you 1 <CLAY> less. Each room costs you 2 <CLAY> less.

name: Sweep
desc: UPDATED: Each time before you use the action space above the most recent round 1-14 action space, you get 2 <CLAY>.

name: Forest Lake Hut
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__/__Forest__ accumulation space, you also get 1 <WOOD>/<FOOD>.

name: Drinking Trough
desc: Each of your pastures (with or without a stable) can hold up to 2 more animals.

name: Cultivator
desc: For each new field tile you get, you also get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Agricultural Labourer
desc: Place 8 <CLAY> on this card. For each <GRAIN> you obtain, you also get 1 <CLAY> from this card.

name: Grain Sieve
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, if you harvest at least 2 <GRAIN>, you get 1 additional <GRAIN> from the general supply.

name: Scrap Collector
desc: Alternate placing 1 <WOOD> and 1 <CLAY> on each of the next 6 round spaces, starting with <WOOD>. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective resource.

name: Mill Wheel
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Utilization__ action space while the __Fishing__ accumulation space is occupied, you get an additional 2 <FOOD>.

name: Catcher
desc: Each time you place your 1st/2nd/3rd person in a round on a building resource accumulation space with exactly 5/4/3 building resources, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Horse-Drawn Boat
desc: Alternate placing 1 <FOOD> and 1 <SHEEP> on each remaining round space, starting with <FOOD>. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Stable Planner
desc: Add 3, 6, and 9 to the current round. You can place 1 stable on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds (not earlier), you can build the stable at no cost.

name: Toolbox
desc: In the work phase, after each turn in which you build at least 1 room, stable, or fence, you can build the __Joinery__, __Pottery__, or __Basketmaker's Workshop__ major improvement.

name: Little Stick Knitter
desc: From Round 5 on, each time you use the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, you can also take a __Family Growth with Room Only__ action.

name: Stone Custodian
desc: At the end of each work phase, you get 1 <FOOD> for each stone accumulation space with stone on it.

name: Sack Cart
desc: Place 1 <GRAIN> each on the remaining spaces for rounds 5, 8, 11, and 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Pan Baker
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Utilization__ action space, you also get 2 <CLAY> and 1 <WOOD>.

name: Tinsmith Master
desc: You can hold 1 additional animal in each pasture without a stable. Each time you sow in a field, you can place 1 additional crop of the respective type in that field.

name: Forest Trader
desc: Each time you use a wood or clay accumulation space, you can also buy exactly 1 building resource. <WOOD>, <CLAY>, and <REED> cost 1 <FOOD> each; <STONE> costs 2 food.

name: Clay Deliveryman
desc: Place 1 <CLAY> on each remaining space for rounds 6 to 14. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CLAY>.

name: Tree Guard
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can place 4 <WOOD> from your supply on that space to get 2 <STONE>, 1 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Butter Churn
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <FOOD> for every 3 <SHEEP> and 1 <FOOD> for every 2 <CATTLE> you have.

name: Archway
desc: This card is an action space for all. A player who uses it immediately gets 1 <FOOD>. Immediately before the returning home phase, they can use an unoccupied action space with the person from this card.

name: Stable Master
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>. Exactly one of your unfenced stables can hold up to 3 animals of one type.

name: Seed Researcher
desc: Each time any people return from both the __Grain Seeds__ and __Vegetable Seeds__ action spaces, you get 2 <FOOD> and you can play 1 occupation, without paying an occupation cost.

name: Freshman
desc: Each time you get a __Bake Bread__ action, instead of taking the action, you can play an occupation without paying an occupation cost (at most once per turn).

name: Site Manager
desc: When you play this card, immediately build a major improvement. When paying its cost, you can replace up to 1 building resource of each type with 1 <FOOD> each.

name: Shepherd's Whistle
desc: At the start of the breeding phase of each harvest, if you have at least 1 unfenced stable without an animal, you get 1 <SHEEP>.

name: Civic Facade
desc: Before the start of each round, if you have more occupations than improvements in your hand, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Plumber
desc: Each time after you use the __Major Improvement__ action space, you can take a __Renovation__ action, paying 2 <CLAY> or 2 <STONE> less for the renovation.

name: Food Chest
desc: If you play this card on the __Major Improvement__ action space, you immediately get 4 <FOOD>. Otherwise, you get only 2 <FOOD>.

name: Maintenance Premium
desc: Place 3 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 1 <FOOD> from this card. Each time you renovate restock this card to 3 <FOOD>.

name: Reed Pond
desc: Place 1 <REED> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <REED>.

name: Chick Stable
desc: Add 3 and 4 to the current round and place 2 <FOOD> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Agricultural Fertilizers
desc: Each time after you turn at least 2 unused spaces into used spaces in one action, you get an additional __Sow__ action.

name: Bonehead
desc: When you play this card, immediately place 6 <WOOD> on it. Immediately after each time you play a card from your hand, including this one, you get 1 <WOOD> from this card.

name: Cesspit
desc: Alternate placing 1 <CLAY> and 1 <PIG> on each remaining round space, starting with <CLAY>. At the start of these rounds, you get the respective good.

name: Truffle Slicer
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if you have at least 1 <PIG>, you can pay 1 <FOOD> for 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Bassinet
desc: You can place a(nother) person on the first non-accumulating action space used in each work phase, if there is only 1 person, including newborns, on that space. (There can never be two people on __Meeting Place__.)

name: Elder Baker
desc: This card is an action space for you only. When you use it, you get 3<GRAIN>. You can build the __Stone Oven__ major improvement even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Large Greenhouse
desc: Add 4, 7, and 9 to the current round and place 1 <VEGETABLE> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <VEGETABLE>.

name: Granary
desc: Place 1 <GRAIN> each on the remaining spaces for rounds 8, 10, and 12. At the start of these rounds, you get the <GRAIN>.

name: Moral Crusader
desc: Immediately before the start of each round, if there are goods on the remaining round spaces that are promised to you, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Nest Site
desc: Each time 1 <REED> is placed on a non-empty __Reed Bank__ accumulation space during the preparation phase, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Chain Float
desc: Add 7, 8, and 9 to the current round and place 1 field on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you can plow the field.

name: Potato Harvester
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 3 <FOOD>. For each <VEGETABLE> you get from your fields during the field phase of the harvest, you get 1 additional <FOOD>.

name: Canoe
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get an additional 1 <FOOD> and 1 <REED>.

name: Beer Keg
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1/2/3 <GRAIN> for 0/1/2 bonus <SCORE> and exactly 3 <FOOD>.

name: Hutch
desc: Place 0, 1, 2, and 3 <FOOD> in this order on the next 4 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Beneficiary
desc: If this is your 3rd occupation, you can immediately play another occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD> and/or play 1 minor improvement by paying its cost.

name: Fruit Ladder
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Flail
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <FOOD>. Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you can also take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Baking Sheet
desc: Each time you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 <GRAIN> for 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Guest Room
desc: Immediately place any amount of <FOOD> from your supply on this card. Once per round, you can discard 1 <FOOD> from this card to place a person from your supply in that round.

name: Portmonger
desc: Each time you take 1/2/3+ <FOOD> from a food accumulation space, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>/<GRAIN>/<REED>.

name: Wheel Plow
desc: Once this game, when you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space with the first person you place in a round, you can plow 2 additional fields.

name: Private Forest
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Drift-Net Boat
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get an additional 2 <FOOD>.

name: Treegardener
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you get 1 <WOOD> and you can buy up to 2 additional <WOOD> for 1 <FOOD> each.

name: Brotherly Love
desc: As long as you have exactly 4 people, in the work phase of each round, you can place your third and fourth person immediately after one another, even on the same action space.

name: Clay Supports
desc: Each time you build a clay room, you can pay 2 <CLAY>, 1 <WOOD>, and 1 <REED> instead of 5 <CLAY> and 2 <REED>.

name: Large Pottery
desc: [Anytime]
<CLAY> <ARROW> 2<FOOD>
[Scoring]
3/5/6/7<CLAY> <ARROW-1X> 1/2/3/4<SCORE>

name: Shovel Bearer
desc: Each time you use the __Clay Pit__ or __Hollow__ accumulation space, you also get a number of <FOOD> equal to the amount of <CLAY> on the respective other accumulation space.

name: Mountain Plowman
desc: Each time you plow at least 1 field, you get 1 <SHEEP> for each field that you just plowed.

name: Threshing Board
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ or __Cultivation__ action space, you get an additional __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Shed Builder
desc: When you build your 1st and 2nd stable, you get 1 <GRAIN>. When you build your 3rd and 4th stable, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>. (This does not apply to stables you have already built.)

name: Stable Tree
desc: Each time you build 1 or more stables on your turn, place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next 3 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Small Greenhouse
desc: Add 4 and 7 to the current round and place 1 <VEGETABLE> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you can buy the <VEGETABLE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Mandoline
desc: Once per round, you can pay 1 <VEGETABLE> to get 1 bonus <SCORE>. If you do, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Tumbrel
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <FOOD>. Each time after you take an unconditional __Sow__ action, you get 1 <FOOD> for each stable you have.

name: Sculptor
desc: Each time you use a clay accumulation space, you also get 1 <FOOD>. Each time you use a stone accumulation space, you also get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Seducer
desc: When you play this card in round 5 or later, you can immediately pay 1 <STONE>, 1 <GRAIN>, 1 <VEGETABLE>, and 1 <SHEEP> to take a __Family Growth Even without Room__ action.

name: Schnapps Distillery
desc: In each feeding phase, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> into 5 <FOOD>. During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> each for your 5th and 6th <VEGETABLE>.

name: Potato Digger
desc: When you play this card, if you have at least 2/4/5 unplanted field tiles, you immediately get 1/2/3 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Seaweed Fertilizer
desc: Each time after you take an unconditional __Sow__ action, you get 1 <GRAIN> from the general supply. From round 11 on, you can get 1 <VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Field Caretaker
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately exchange 0/1/3 <CLAY> for 1/2/3 <GRAIN>. This card is a field.

name: Sour Dough
desc: Once per round, if all players have at least 1 person left to place, you can skip placing a person and take a __Bake Bread__ action instead.

name: Lieutenant General
desc: For each field tile that another player places next to an existing field tile, you get 1 <FOOD> from the general supply. In round 14, you get 1 <GRAIN> instead.

name: Early Cattle
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <CATTLE>.

name: Prophet
desc: When you play this card, immediately take a __Renovation__ action. Afterward, you can take a __Build Fences__ action. (Both actions require their usual cost.)

name: Bale of Straw
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 3 grain fields (including field cards with planted grain), you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Comb and Cutter
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get 1 additional <FOOD> for each <SHEEP> on the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, up to a maximum of 4 additional <FOOD>.

name: Clay Plasterer
desc: Renovating to clay only costs you exactly 1 <CLAY> and 1 <REED>. Each clay room only costs you 3 <CLAY> and 2 <REED> to build.

name: Braid Maker
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1 <REED> for 2 <FOOD>. You can build the  __Basketmaker's Workshop__ for 1 <REED> and 1 <STONE> even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Supply Boat
desc: Each time after you use the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you can choose to buy 1 <GRAIN> for 1 <FOOD>, or 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>.

name: Cookery Outfitter
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each cooking improvement you have. (Ovens are not considered cooking improvements.)

name: Cottar
desc: Each time you play or build an improvement, you get your choice of 1 <WOOD> or 1 <CLAY> immediately after paying its cost.

name: Claw Knife
desc: Each time you use the __Sheep Market__ accumulation space, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Animal Bedding
desc: You can keep 1 additional animal (of the same type) in each of your unfenced stables, and 2 additional animals (of the same type) in each pasture with stable.

name: Butler
desc: If you play this card in round 11 or before, during scoring, you get 4 bonus <SCORE> if you then have more rooms than people.

name: Patch Caregiver
