desc: When you play this card, you can choose to buy 1 <GRAIN> for 1 <FOOD>, or 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>. This card is a field.

name: Riverine Shepherd
desc: Each time you use the __Sheep Market__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you can also take 1 good from the respective other accumulation space, if possible.

name: Paintbrush
desc: Each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 <CLAY> for your choice of 2 <FOOD> or 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Tax Collector
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you get your choice of 2 <WOOD>, 2 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, or 1 <STONE>.

name: Hill Cultivator
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ or __Vegetable Seeds__ action space, you also get 2 or 3 <CLAY>, respectively.

name: Rustic
desc: For each clay room you build, you get 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>. (this does not apply to stone rooms and renovated wood rooms.)

name: Pavior
desc: At the end of each preparation phase, if you have at least 1 <STONE> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD>. In round 14, you get 1 <VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Water Worker
desc: Each time after you use any of the __Fishing__, __Reed Bank__, __Day Laborer__ spaces or the action space of round 4, you get 1 additional <REED>.

name: Wood Cart
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get 2 additional <WOOD>.

name: Interior Decorator
desc: Each time you renovate, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 6 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Steam Plow
desc: Immediately after each returning home phase, you can pay 2 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD> to use the __Farmland__ action space without placing a person.

name: Soil Scientist
desc: Each time after you use a clay/stone accumulation space, you can place 1 <STONE>/2 <CLAY> from your supply on the space to get 2 <GRAIN>/1 <VEGETABLE>, respectively.

name: Slurry
desc: In the breeding phase of each harvest, if you get newborn animals of at least two types, you also get a __Sow__ action.

name: Calcium Fertilizers
desc: Each time you use a __Quarry__ accumulation space, add 1 additional good of the respective type to each of your planted fields growing a single type of crop.

name: Market Stall
desc: After the field phase of each harvest, you can exchange 1 <GRAIN> plus 1 <FENCE> (both from your supply) for 5 <FOOD>.

name: Hod
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <CLAY>. Each time any player (including you) uses the __Pig Market__ accumulation space, you immediately get 2 <CLAY>.

name: Waterlily Pond
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Carpenter's Axe
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, if you then have at least 7 <WOOD> in your supply, you can build exactly 1 stable for 1 <WOOD>.

name: Pipe Smoker
desc: At the start of each harvest, if you have at least 1 grain field, you get 2<WOOD>.

name: Land Heir
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, place 4 <WOOD> and 4 <CLAY> on the space for round 9. At the start of this round, you get the resources.

name: Abort Oriel
desc: You can no longer play this card when any player (including you) has 5 or more cards in front of them.

name: Godly Spouse
desc: Each time you take a __Family Growth__ action with the second person you place in a round, return the first person you placed home, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Pasture Master
desc: Each time you renovate, you get 2 <FOOD> and 1 additional animal of the respective type in each of your pastures with stable.

name: Family Friendly Home
desc: Each time you take a __Build Rooms__ action while having more rooms than people already, you also get a __Family Growth__ action and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Trellises
desc: Immediately place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of fences you have built. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Ravenous Hunger
desc: Immediately after each time you use the __Vegetable Seeds__ action space, you can place another person on an accumulation space and get 1 additional good of the accumulating type.

name: Tasting
desc: Each time you use a __Lessons__ action space, before paying the occupation cost, you can exchange 1 <GRAIN> for 4 <FOOD>.

name: Excavator
desc: Each time after you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you get 1 additional <WOOD> and <CLAY>, and you can buy 1 <STONE> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Hauberg
desc: Alternate placing 2 <WOOD> and 1 <PIG> on the next 4 round spaces. You decide what to start with. At the start of these rounds, you get the goods.

name: Oven Firing Boy
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, you get an additional __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Field Merchant
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <REED>. Each time you decline a __Minor/Major Improvement__ action, you get 1 <FOOD>/<VEGETABLE> instead.

name: Walking Boots
desc: You immediately get 2 <FOOD>. You must immediately place a person from your supply. If you do, in the next returning home phase, you must remove that person from play.

name: Informant
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. After each work phase, if you have more <STONE> than <CLAY> in your supply, you get 1 <WOOD>.

name: Nightworker
desc: Before the start of each work phase, you can place a person on an accumulation space of a building resource not in your supply. (Then proceed with the start player.)

name: Prodigy
desc: If this is your 1st occupation, you immediately get 1 <SCORE> for each improvement you have. (This will not apply to improvements played after this card.)

name: Merchant
desc: Immediately after each time you take a __Major or Minor Improvement__ or __Minor Improvement__ action, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to take the action a second time.

name: Market Master
desc: Immediately after each time you place your last person in a round on the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can play 1 occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Little Peasant
desc: You immediately get 1 <STONE>. As long as you live in a wooden house with exactly 2 rooms, actions spacesexcluding Meeting Placeare not considered occupied for you.

name: Canvas Sack
desc: When you play this card paying <GRAIN>/<REED> for it, you immediately get 1 <VEGETABLE>/4 <WOOD>.

name: Patron
desc: Immediately before each time you play an occupation after this one (even before paying the occupation cost), you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Stone Cart
desc: Place 1 <STONE> on each remaining even-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <STONE>.

name: Final Scenario
desc: UPDATED: Reveal the action space card for round 14. Only you can use it until round 14 starts.

name: Craft Brewery
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to exchange 1 <GRAIN> from your supply plus 1 <GRAIN> from a field for 2 bonus <SCORE> and 4 <FOOD>.

name: Forestry Studies
desc: Each time after you use the __Forest__ accumulation space, you can return 2 <WOOD> to that space to play 1 occupation without paying an occupation costs.

name: Harpooner
desc: Each time you use the __Fishing__ space you can also pay 1 <WOOD> to get 1 <FOOD> for each person you have, and 1 <REED>

name: Bookmark
desc: Add 3 to the current round and mark the corresponding round space. At the start of that round, you can play 1 occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Stable Milker
desc: Each time you build at least 2 stables on the same turn, you also get 1 <CATTLE>.

name: Art Teacher
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <REED>. Each time you pay an occupation cost, you can use <FOOD> from the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space.

name: House Steward
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most rooms gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Craft Teacher
desc: Each time after you build the major improvement __Joinery__, __Pottery__, and __Basketmaker's Workshop__, you can play up to 2 occupations without paying an occupation cost.

name: Royal Wood
desc: At the end of each turn in which you use the __Farm Expansion__ action space or build an improvement, you get 1 <WOOD> back for every 2 <WOOD> paid during those actions (rounded down).

name: Cooperative Plower
desc: Each time you use the __Farmland__ action space while the __Grain Seeds__ action space is occupied, you can plow 1 additional field.

name: Lazybones
desc: Place (up to) 1 <STABLE> each on __Grain Seeds__, __Farmland__, __Day Laborer__, and __Farm Expansion__. Build the <STABLE> at no cost when another player uses that action space.

name: Weakling
desc: Each time it is your turn in the work phase, if there are one or more accumulation spaces with 5+ goods on them and you do not use any of them, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Stone Importer
desc: In the breeding phase of the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th harvest, you can use this card to buy exactly 2 <STONE> for 2/2/3/3/4/1 <FOOD>.

name: Hardworking Man
desc: This card is an action space for you only. If each other player has more rooms than you, it provides the __Day Laborer__, __Building Rooms__, and __Major Improvement__ actions (all three).

name: Forest Reviewer
desc: Each time after any player (including you) uses the unoccupied __Grove__ or __Forest__ accumulation space while the other of the two is occupied, you get 1 <REED>.

name: Furniture Maker
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Each time you play an occupation after this one, you get 1 <WOOD> for each <FOOD> paid as occupation cost.

name: Food Distributor
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN> and, at the start of this returning home phase, an amount of <FOOD> equal to the number of occupied Round 1-14 action spaces.

name: Emergency Seller
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately turn as many building resources into food as you have people:
<WOOD>/<CLAY> <ARROW> 2 <FOOD>
<REED>/<STONE> <ARROW> 3 <FOOD>

name: Field Doctor
desc: Once this game, if you live in a house with exactly 2 rooms surrounded by 4 field tiles, you can use any __Wish for Children__ action space even without room.

name: Drudgery Reeve
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with 1+/2+/3+ building resources of each type gets 1/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Junior Artist
desc: Each time after you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to use an unoccupied __Traveling Players__ or __Lessons__ action space with the same person.

name: Ranch Provost
desc: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with a pasture of highest capacity gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Cubbyhole
desc: For each room that you add to your house, place 1 <FOOD> from the general supply on this card. At the start of each feeding phase, you get <FOOD> equal to the amount on this card.

name: Charcoal Burner
desc: Each time any player (including you) plays or builds a <BAKE>-improvement, you get 1 <WOOD> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Animal Husbandry Worker
desc: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 <WOOD> and a __Build Fences__ action. During scoring, each player with the most pastures gets 2 <SCORE>.

name: Turnip Farmer
desc: At the start of the returning home phase of each round, if both the __Day Laborer__ and __Grain Seeds__ action spaces are occupied, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Pub Owner
desc: When you play this card and at the end of each work phase in which the __Forest__, __Clay Pit__, and __Reed Bank__ accumulation spaces are all occupied, you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Debt Security
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each major improvement you have, up to the number of your unused farmyard spaces.

name: Pure Breeder
desc: You immediately get 1 <WOOD>. After each round that does not end with a harvest, you can breed exactly one type of animal. (This is not considered a breeding phase.)

name: Forest Guardian
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <WOOD>. Each time before another player takes at least 5 <WOOD> from an accumulation space, they must first pay you 1 <FOOD>.

name: Joiner of the Sea
desc: Each time another player uses the __Fishing__/__Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you can give them 1 <WOOD> to get 2 <FOOD>/3 <FOOD> from the general supply.

name: Seed Seller
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <GRAIN>. Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you get 1 additional <GRAIN>.

name: Pickler
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most total <VEGETABLE> gets 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Animal Reeve
desc: If there are still 1/3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 1/2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with 2/3/4+ animals of each type gets 1/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Transactor
desc: Immediately before the final harvest at the end of round 14, you can take all the building resources that are left on the entire game board.

name: Elder
desc: You can play this card at the start of the work phase of round 1 without placing a person. (This card has no effect other than counting as a played occupation.)

name: Forest Clearer
desc: Each time you obtain exactly 2/3/4 <WOOD> from a wood accumulation space, you get 1 additional <WOOD> and 1/0/1 <FOOD>.

name: Forest Tallyman
desc: Each time both the __Forest__ and __Clay Pit__ accumulation spaces are occupied, you can use this card as an action space to get 2 <CLAY> and 3 <WOOD>.

name: Puppeteer
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can pay them 1 <FOOD> to immediately play an occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Ropemaker
desc: At the end of each harvest, you get 1 <REED> from the general supply.

name: Cattle Whisperer
desc: Add 5 and 8 to the current round and place 1 <CATTLE> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <CATTLE>.

name: Scales
desc: Each time after you place an improvement or occupation in front of you, if you then have the same number of improvements and occupations in play, you get 2 <FOOD>.

name: Outskirts Director
desc: Each time you use the __Grove__ or __Hollow__ accumulation space, you can place 2 <REED> from the general supply on the other space. If you do, you can immediately place another person.

name: Begging Student
desc: When you play this card, you must immediately take 1 <BEGGING> marker. At the start of each harvest, you can play 1 occupation without paying an occupation cost.

name: Mummy's Boy
desc: Once per round, when placing a person after your first two, you can place it on the action space with your 2nd person and use that space again, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Conjurer
desc: Each time you use the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you get an additional 1 <WOOD> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Basket
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can exchange 2 <WOOD> for 3 <FOOD>. If you do, place those 2 <WOOD> on the accumulation space.

name: Brushwood Collector
desc: Each time you renovate or build a room, you can replace the required 1 or 2 <REED> with a total of 1 <WOOD>.

name: Bohemian
desc: At the start of each returning home phase, if at least one __Lessons__ action space is unoccupied, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Childless
desc: At the start of each round, if you have at least 3 rooms but only 2 people, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 crop of your choice (<GRAIN> or <VEGETABLE>)

name: Contraband
desc: Each time you play or build an improvement after this, you can pay 1 additional building resource of a type in the printed cost to get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Sheep Whisperer
desc: Add 2, 5, 8, and 10 to the current round and place 1 <SHEEP> on each corresponding round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <SHEEP>.

name: Lantern House
desc: During scoring, you get 1 negative <SCORE> for each card left in your hand. You cannot discard cards from your hand unplayed. If you already have, you cannot play this card.

name: Beer Table
desc: At the end of the field phase of each harvest, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> from your supply to get 2 bonus <SCORE>. If you do, all other players get 1 <FOOD> each.

name: Beer Tent Operator
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn 1 <WOOD> plus 1 <GRAIN> into 1 bonus <SCORE> and 2 <FOOD>.

name: Miller
desc: You can immediately build a <BAKE>-improvement by paying its cost. Each time another player uses the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Future Building Site
desc: Up until all other farmyard spaces are used, you cannot use the unused spaces that are orthogonally adjacent to your house (not even to build rooms).

name: Midwife
desc: Each time another player uses the first person they place in a round to take a __Family Growth__ action, you get 1 <GRAIN> from the general supply.

name: Cordmaker
desc: Each time any player (including you) takes at least 2 <REED> from the __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you can choose to take 1 <GRAIN> or buy 1 <VEGETABLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Clay Warden
desc: Each time another player uses the __Hollow__ accumulation space, you get 1 <CLAY>. In a 3-/4-player game, you also get 1 additional <CLAY>/<FOOD>.

name: Job Contract
desc: If both are unoccupied, you can use the __Day Laborer__ and the adjacent __Lessons__ action space with a single person (in that order). Afterward, both spaces are considered occupied.

name: Piggy Bank
desc: At the end of each work phase, you can place 1 <FOOD> on this card, irretrievably. At any time, you can discard 6 <FOOD> from this card to build a major improvement at no cost.

name: Wood Collector
desc: Place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next 5 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Mattock
desc: Each time you get <REED> and/or <STONE> from an action space, you get 1 additional <CLAY>.

name: Schnapps Distiller
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <VEGETABLE> into 5 <FOOD>.

name: Flax Farmer
desc: Each time you use the __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you also get 1<GRAIN>. Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you also get 1 <REED>.

name: Illusionist
desc: Each time you use a building resource accumulation space, you can discard exactly 1 card from your hand to get 1 additional building resource of the accumulating type.

name: Beer Stein
desc: Each time you take a __Bake Bread__ action, you can use this card once to turn 1 <GRAIN> into 2 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Asparagus Knife
desc: In the returning home phase of rounds 8, 10, and 12, you can take 1 <VEGETABLE> from exactly 1 vegetable field. You can immediately exchange it for 3 <FOOD> and 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Bargain Hunter
desc: At the start of each round, you can place 1 <FOOD> from your supply on the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space to play a minor improvement by paying its cost.

name: Swagman
desc: Immediately after each time you use the __Farm Expansion__ or __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can use the respective other space with the same person (even if it is occupied).

name: Chairman
desc: Each time another player uses the __Meeting Place__ action space, both they and you get 1 <FOOD> (before taking the actions). If you use it, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Bunny Breeder
desc: Select a future round space, subtract the number of the current round from it, and place this many <FOOD> on that space. At the start of that round, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Thresher
desc: Immediately before each time you use the __Grain Utilization__, __Farmland__, or __Cultivation__ action space, you can buy 1 <GRAIN> for 1 <FOOD>.

name: Potato Planter
desc: At the end of each work phase in which you occupy the __Clay Pit__ or __Reed Bank__ accumulation space while the respective other is unoccupied, you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Fodder Beets
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining odd-numbered round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Pet Lover
desc: Each time you use an accumulation space providing exactly 1 animal, you can leave it on the space and get one from the general supply instead, as well as 3 <FOOD> and 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Animal Activist
desc: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most fenced stables gets 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Parvenu
desc: If you play this card in round 7 or before, choose <CLAY> or <REED>: you immediately get a number of that building resource equal to the number you already have in your supply.

name: Recluse
desc: As long as you have no minor improvements in front of you, you get 1 <FOOD> at the start of each round and 1 <WOOD> at the start of each harvest.

name: House Artist
desc: Each time you use the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you also get a __Build Rooms__ action. Each room you build during the action costs you 1 <REED> less.

name: Beer Tap
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <FOOD>. In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can turn 2/3/4 <GRAIN> into 3/6/9 <FOOD>.

name: Collier
desc: Each time after you use the __Clay Pit__ or __Hollow__ accumulation space, you get 1 <WOOD>. On __Clay Pit__ you also get 1 additional <REED>.

name: Veggie Lover
desc: [Harvest]
<GRAIN_VEG_STACK> <ARROW-1X> 6<FOOD>
[Scoring]
1/2/3 <GRAIN_VEG_STACK> <ARROW-1X> 2/4/6 <SCORE>

name: Woodcraft
desc: Each time you use a wood accumulation space, if immediately afterward you have at most 5 <WOOD> in your supply, you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Crack Weeder
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>. For each <VEGETABLE> you take from a field in the field phase of a harvest, you also get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Studio
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, you can use this card to turn exactly 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<STONE> into 2/2/3 <FOOD>.

name: Plow Builder
desc: You can build the Joinery when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action. If you use the Joinery (or an upgrade thereof) during the harvest, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Mantlepiece
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each complete round left to play. You may no longer renovate your house.

name: Misanthropy
desc: During scoring, if you have exactly 4/3/2 people, you get 2/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Woolgrower
desc: This card can hold a number of <SHEEP> equal to the number of completed feeding phases.

name: Tree Inspector
desc: This card is a __1 <WOOD>__ accumulation space for you only. Each time the newly revealed action space card is a __Quarry__ accumulation space, you must discard all <WOOD> from this card.

name: Breeder Buyer
desc: Each time you build at least 1 wood/clay/stone room and at least 1 stable on the same turn, you also get 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE>.

name: Animal Feeder
desc: On the __Day Laborer__ action space, you also get your choice of 1 <SHEEP> or 1 <GRAIN>. Instead of that good, you can buy 1 <PIG> for 1 <FOOD> or 1 <CATTLE> for 2 <FOOD>.

name: Kelp Gatherer
desc: Each time another player uses the __Fishing__ accumulation space, they get 1 additional <FOOD> and you get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Stone Sculptor
desc: Each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 <STONE> for 1 bonus <SCORE> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Interim Storage
desc: Each time you use a clay/reed/stone accumulation space, place 1 <WOOD>/<CLAY>/<REED> on this card. At the start of rounds 7, 11, and 14, move all the goods on this card to your supply.

name: Mud Wallower
desc: Every fourth time you use an accumulation space, you get 1 <PIG>, held by this card.

name: Wares Salesman
desc: Each time any player (including you) plays or builds a card that lets them turn building resources into <FOOD>, you get exactly 1 corresponding building resource and 1 <REED>.

name: Animal Teacher
desc: Immediately after each time you use a __Lessons__ action space, you can also buy 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> for 0/1/2 <FOOD>.

name: Carter
desc: Next round, each time you use a building resource accumulation space, you also get 1 <FOOD> for each building resource that you take from the space.

name: Stonecutter
desc: Every improvement, room, and renovation costs you 1 <STONE> less.

name: Trap Builder
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, place 1 <FOOD>, 1 <FOOD>, and 1 <PIG> on the next 3 round spaces, respectively. At the start of these rounds, you get the good.

name: Spin Doctor
desc: Immediately after each time you use the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can place another person on an action space of your choice, regardless whether or not the action space is occupied.

name: Hawktower
desc: Place a stone room on round space 12. If you live in a stone house at the start of the round, you can build the stone room at no cost. Otherwise, discard the stone room.

name: Blackberry Farmer
desc: Each time you build fences, place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining round space, up to the number of fences just built. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Studio Boat
desc: Each time you use the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you also get 1 bonus <SCORE>. In games with 1-3 players, this card is considered __Traveling Players__ (same effect as __Fishing__).

name: Domestician Expert
desc: You can keep 2 sheep on the border between each pair of orthogonally adjacent rooms.

name: Gardening Head Official
desc: If there are still 3/6/9 complete rounds left to play, you immediately get 2/3/4 <WOOD>. During scoring, each player with the most vegetables in their fields gets 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Whale Oil
desc: Each time you use __Fishing__, place 1 <FOOD> from the general supply on this card. Each time before you play an occupation, you get <FOOD> equal to the amount on this card.

name: Forest Inn
desc: This is an action space for all. A player who uses it can exchange 5/7/9 <WOOD> for 8 <WOOD> and 2/4/7 <FOOD>. When another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 <FOOD>.

name: Scholar
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>, or a minor improvement (by paying its cost).

name: Firewood
desc: UPDATED: In the returning home phase of each round, place 1 <WOOD> on this card. Each time after you build a Fireplace, Cooking Hearth, or oven, move up to 4 <WOOD> from this card to your supply.

name: Harvest House
desc: When you play this card, if the number of completed harvests is equal to the number of occupations you played, you immediately get 1 <FOOD>, 1 <GRAIN>, and 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Sowing Director
desc: Each time after another player uses the __Grain Utilization__ action space, you get a __Sow__ action.

name: Old Miser
desc: In the feeding phase of each harvest, each of your people requires 1less <FOOD>. During scoring, your people are worth 2 points each instead of 3.

name: Overachiever
desc: Each time you use a __Wish for Children__ action space, you can play 1 additional improvement by paying its cost minus 1 resource of your choice.

name: Stagehand
desc: Each time another player uses the __Traveling Players__ accumulation space, you can take your choice of a __Build Fences__, __Build Stables__, or __Build Rooms__ action.

name: Claypit Owner
desc: Each time another player plays or builds an improvement with a printed <CLAY> cost, you get 1 <FOOD> and 1 <CLAY>.

name: Acquirer
desc: At the start of each round, you can pay <FOOD> equal to the number of people you have to buy 1 good of your choice from the general supply.

name: Master Tanner
desc: For each <PIG> or <CATTLE> you turn into <FOOD>, you can place 1 of that <FOOD> on this card. While its <FOOD> equals your number of rooms, this card provides room for 1 person.

name: Freemason
desc: As long as you live in a <CLAY>/<STONE> house with exactly 2 rooms, at the start of each work phase, you get 2 <CLAY>/<STONE>.

name: Market Crier
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space, you can get an additional 1 <GRAIN> and 1 <VEGETABLE>. If you do, each other player gets 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Visionary
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, you get 1 <STONE>, 1<VEGETABLE>, and 2 <PIG>. You cannot grow your family until round 11, unless all other players already have.

name: Recreational Carpenter
desc: At the end of each work phase in which you did not use the __Meeting Place__ action space, you can take a __Build Rooms__ action without placing a person.

name: Hollow Warden
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get a __Major Improvement__ action to build a Fireplace. Each time you use the __Hollow__ accumulation space, you also get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Straw Hat
desc: At the end of the work phases of rounds 3 and 6, you can move your person from the __Farmland__ action space to an unoccupied action space and take that action, or get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Parrot Breeder
desc: On your turn, if you pay 1 <GRAIN> to the general supply, you can use the same action space (unless it is the __Meeting Place__ action space) that the player to your right has just used on their turn (not retroactive).

name: Lodger
desc: This card provides room for one person, but only until the returning home phase of round 9. If, by then, there is no room elsewhere for that person, remove it from play.

name: Private Teacher
desc: Each time you use the __Grain Seeds__ action space when any __Lessons__ action space is occupied, you can also play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Building Tycoon
desc: Each time after another player builds 1 or more rooms, you can give them 1 <FOOD> to build exactly 1 room yourself. (You must pay the building cost of the room.)

name: Earthenware Potter
desc: If you play this card in round 4 or before, after the final harvest, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each person for which you then pay 1 <CLAY>.

name: Rock Beater
desc: You can use an action space providing both stone and a different building resource even if it is occupied by another player. Stone rooms cost you 2 <STONE> less each.

name: Wooden Shed
desc: This card can only be played via a __Major Improvement__ action. It provides room for one person. You may no longer renovate.

name: Riparian Builder
desc: Each time another player uses the __Reed Bank__ accumulation space, you can build a room: if you build a clay/stone room, you get a discount of 1 <CLAY>/2 <STONE>.

name: Lumber Virtuoso
desc: Each harvest in which you have at least 5 <WOOD> in your supply, you can discard down to 5 <WOOD> to take a __Build Stables__ or __Build Wood Rooms__ action by paying the usual costs.

name: Saddler
desc: Each time after you build a major improvement, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to plow 1 field.

name: Clay Deposit
desc: Immediately after each time you use a clay accumulation space, you can exchange 1 <CLAY> for 1 bonus <SCORE>. If you do, place the <CLAY> on the accumulation space.

name: Minstrel
desc: At the start of each returning home phase, if only one action space card on round space 1 to 4 is unoccupied, you can use that action space.

name: Hayloft Barn
desc: Place 4 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you obtain at least 1 <GRAIN>, you also get 1 <FOOD> from this card. Once it is empty, you get a __Family Growth Even without Room__ action.

name: Bookshelf
desc: Immediately before each time you play an occupation (even before paying the occupation cost), you get 3 <FOOD>.

name: Equipper
desc: Immediately after each time you use a wood accumulation space, you can play a minor improvement.

name: Pastor
desc: Once you are the only player to live in a house with only 2 rooms, you immediately get 3 <WOOD>, 2 <CLAY>, 1 <REED>, and 1 <STONE> (only once).

name: Autumn Mother
desc: Immediately before each harvest, if you have room in your house, you can take a __Family Growth__ action for 3 <FOOD>.

name: Retail Dealer
desc: Place 3 <GRAIN> and 3 <FOOD> on this card. Each time you use the __Resource Market__ action space, you also get 1 <GRAIN> and 1 <FOOD> from this card.

name: Wealthy Man
desc: At the start of each of the 1st/2nd/3rd/4th/5th/6th harvest, if you have at least 1/2/3/4/5/6 grain fields, you get 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Manservant
desc: Once you live in a stone house, place 3 <FOOD> on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Small Animal Breeder
desc: Before the start of each round, if you have <FOOD> equal to or higher than the upcoming round number (e.g., 8+ <FOOD> before round 8), you get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Land Surveyor
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, if you have at least 2/4/6/7 fields, you get 1/2/3/4 <FOOD>.

name: Changeover
desc: At any time, if a field contains exactly 1 good as a result of a harvest, you can discard that good and immediately take a __Sow__ action limited to that field.

name: Basket Chair
desc: When you play this card, you can immediately move the first person (unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space) you placed this work phase to this card. If you do, immediately afterward, you can place another person.

name: Forest Plow
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can pay 2 <WOOD> to plow 1 field. Place the paid <WOOD> on the accumulation space (for the next visitor).

name: Dwelling Mound
desc: From now on, you must pay 1 <FOOD> for each new field tile that you place in your farmyard.

name: Tree Cutter
desc: Each time you use an accumulation space providing at least 3 goods of the same type except <WOOD>, you get an additional 1 <WOOD>. (<FOOD> is also considered a good.)

name: Wholesaler
desc: Place 1 <VEGETABLE>, 1 <PIG>, 1 <STONE>, and 1 <CATTLE> on this card. Each time you use an action space card on round spaces 8 to 11, you get the corresponding good from this card.

name: Seatmate
desc: You can use the action space on round space 13 even if it is occupied by one or more people of the players to your immediate left and right.

name: Simple Oven
desc: [__Bake Bread__ action:]
<GRAIN> <ARROW-1X> 3<FOOD>
When you play this card, you can immediately take a __Bake Bread__ action.

name: Raised Bed
desc: At the start of each harvest, you get 4 <FOOD>.

name: Pulverizer Plow
desc: Immediately after each time you use a clay accumulation space, you can pay 1 <CLAY> to plow 1 field. If you do, place that 1 <CLAY> on the accumulation space.

name: Wood Rake
desc: During scoring, if you had at least 7 goods in your fields before the final harvest, you get 2 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Wood Carrier
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <WOOD> for each improvement in front of you.

name: Estate Master
desc: Once you have no unused farmyard spaces left, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each <VEGETABLE> that you harvest.

name: Bellfounder
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have at least 1 <CLAY>, you can use this card to discard all of your <CLAY> and get your choice of 3 <FOOD> or 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Entrepreneur
desc: At the start of each round, you can move 1 <FOOD> to this card or discard 1 <FOOD> from it. If you do either, you get 1 building resource of a type you currently do not have.

name: Patroness
desc: Each time after you play an occupation after this one, you get 1 building resource of your choice.

name: Stable Manure
desc: In the field phase of each harvest, you can harvest 1 additional good from a number of fields equal to the number of unfenced stables you have.

name: Teacher's Desk
desc: Each time you use the __Major Improvement__ or __House Redevelopment__ action space, you can also play 1 occupation at an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Pottery Yard
desc: During the scoring, if there are at least 2 orthogonally adjacent unused spaces in your farm, you get 2 bonus <SCORE>. (You still get the negative points for those unused spaces.

name: Sheep Inspector
desc: Once per work phase, after you complete a person action, you can pay 1 <SHEEP> and 2 <FOOD> to return another person you placed home, unless it is on the __Meeting Place__ action space.

name: Stable Sergeant
desc: When you play this card, you can pay 2 <FOOD> to get 1 <SHEEP>, 1 <PIG>, and 1 <CATTLE>, but only if you can accommodate all three animals on your farm.

name: Briar Hedge
desc: You do not need to pay wood for fences that you build on the edge of your farmyard board.

name: Syrup Tap
desc: Each time you get at least 1 <WOOD> from an action space, place 1 <FOOD> on the next round space. At the start of that round, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Big Country
desc: For each complete round left to play, you immediately get 1 bonus <SCORE> and 2 <FOOD>.

name: Master Builder
desc: Once your house has at least 5 rooms, at any time, but only once this game, you can add another room at no cost.

name: Half-Timbered House
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each stone room you have. You can only use one card to get bonus points for your stone house.

name: Housemaster
desc: During scoring, total the base point values of your major improvements. The smallest value counts double. If the total is at least 5/7/9/11, you get 1/2/3/4 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Farm Store
desc: After the feeding phase of each harvest, you can exchange exactly 1 <FOOD> for 2 different building resources of your choice or 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Wood Worker
desc: Each time you take <WOOD> from an accumulation space, you can exchange 1 <WOOD> for 1 <SHEEP>. Place the <WOOD> on the accumulation space.

name: Casual Worker
desc: Each time another player uses a __Quarry__ accumulation space, you can choose to get 1 <FOOD> or build a stable without paying wood.

name: Vegetable Vendor
desc: Each time you use the __Major Improvement__ or __Vegetable Seeds__ action space, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE> or a __Major or Minor Improvement__ action, respectively.

name: Heart of Stone
desc: Each time a __Quarry__ accumulation space is revealed, if you have room in your house, you can immediately take a __Family Growth__ action without placing a person.

name: Hewer
desc: From round 3 on, at the end of each work phase in which all clay accumulation spaces are unoccupied, you get 1 <STONE> and 1 <FOOD>.

name: Cookery Lesson
desc: Each time you use a __Lessons__ action space and a cooking improvement on the same turn, you get 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Huntsman
desc: Each time after you use a wood accumulation space, you can pay 1 <GRAIN> to get 1 <PIG>.

name: Haydryer
desc: Immediately before each harvest, you can buy 1 <CATTLE> for 4 <FOOD> minus 1 <FOOD> for each pasture you have. (The minimum cost is 0).

name: Wholesale Market
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining round space. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Game Catcher
desc: When you play this card, pay 1 <FOOD> for each remaining harvest to immediately get 1 <CATTLE> and 1 <PIG>.

name: Chapel
desc: This is an action space for all. A player who uses it gets 3 bonus <SCORE>. If another player uses it, they must first pay you 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Writing Chamber
desc: During scoring, you get a number of bonus <SCORE> equal to the total of negative points you have, to a maximum of 7 <SCORE>.

name: Craftsmanship Promoter
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 <STONE>. You can build any of the major improvements in the bottom row of the supply board even when taking a __Minor Improvement__ action.

name: Night-School Student
desc: Each returning home phase in which no player returns a person from a __Lessons__ action space, you can play an occupation for an occupation cost of 1 <FOOD>.

name: Case Builder
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 1 good of each of the following types, if you have at least 2 of that good in your supply already: <FOOD>, <GRAIN>, <VEGETABLE>, <REED>, <WOOD>.

name: Food Merchant
desc: For each <GRAIN> you harvest from a field, you can buy 1 <VEGETABLE> for 3 <FOOD>. If you harvest the last <GRAIN> from a field, the <VEGETABLE> costs you only 2 <FOOD>.

name: Fisherman's Friend
desc: At the start of each round, if there is more <FOOD> on the __Traveling Players__ than on the __Fishing__ accumulation space, you get the difference from the general supply.

name: Master Fencer
desc: Once you live in a stone house, at the start of each round, you can pay 2 or 3 <WOOD> to build up to 3 or 4 fences, respectively.

name: Potters Market
desc: At any time, you can pay 3 <CLAY> and 2 <FOOD>. If you do, place 1 <VEGETABLE> on each of the next 2 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <VEGETABLE>.

name: German Heath Keeper
desc: Each time any player (including you) uses the __Pig Market__ accumulation space, you get 1 <SHEEP> from the general supply.

name: Telegram
desc: Add 1 to the current round for each fence in your supply and mark the corresponding round space. In that round only, you can place a person from your supply.

name: Buyer
desc: Each time another player uses a reed, stone, sheep, or wild boar accumulation space, you can pay them 1 <FOOD> to get 1 good of the respective type from the general supply.

name: Bed in the Grain Field
desc: At the start of the next harvest, you get a __Family Growth__ action if you have room for the newborn.

name: Outrider
desc: Each time before you use the action space on the most recently revealed action space card (after it has been placed on the round space), you get 1 <GRAIN>.

name: Summer House
desc: During scoring, if you live in a stone house, you get 2 bonus <SCORE> for each unused farmyard space orthogonally adjacent to your house. (You still lose the points for these unused spaces.)

name: Silage
desc: In each returning home phase after which there is no harvest, you can pay exactly 1 <GRAIN> - even from a field - to breed exactly one type of animal.

name: Midnight Fencer
desc: At the start of the last harvest, you can take up to 2 of each other player's unbuilt fences and build them on your farm at no cost. (Your farm can then have over 15 fences.)

name: Second Spouse
desc: You can use the __Urgent Wish for Children__ action space (from round 12-13) even if it is occupied by the first person another player placed.

name: Facades Carving
desc: When you play this card, you can exchange any number of <FOOD> for 1 bonus <SCORE> each, up to the number of completed harvests.
prerequisite: Wood in Your Supply >= Current Round

name: Greening Plan
desc: During scoring, if you then have at least 2/4/5/6 unplanted fields, you get 1/2/3/5 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Reed Roof Renovator
desc: Each time another player renovates, you immediately get 1 <REED> from the general supply. When you play this card in a 3-player game, you immediately get 1 <REED>.

name: Oyster Eater
desc: Each time the __Fishing__ accumulation space is used, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> and must skip placing your next person that round. (You can place the person on a later turn.)

name: Mason
desc: Place a stone room on this card. Once you have a stone house with at least 4 rooms, at any time, you can add that room without paying any building resources.

name: Storehouse Steward
desc: Each time you take exactly 2/3/4/5 <FOOD> from a food accumulation space, you also get 1 <STONE>/<REED>/<CLAY>/<WOOD>. (If you take 6 or more <FOOD>, you do not get a bonus good).

name: Lunchtime Beer
desc: At the start of each harvest, you can choose to skip the field and breeding phase of that harvest and get exactly 1 <FOOD> instead.

name: Journeyman Bricklayer
desc: When you play this card, you immediately get 2 <STONE>. Each time another player renovates to stone or builds a stone room, you get 1 <STONE>.

name: Diligent Farmer
desc: When you play this card, if you would score the maximum 4 points in 3 scoring categories (including fenced stables), you can extend your house by 1 room at no cost.

name: Patch Caretaker
desc: Each time you use an accumulation space while already having used another accumulation space for the same type of good that work phase, you also get 1 <VEGETABLE>.

name: Animal Catcher
desc: Each time you use the __Day Laborer__ action space, instead of 2 <FOOD>, you can get 3 different animals from the general supply. If you do, you must pay 1 <FOOD> each harvest left to play.

name: Sheep Keeper
desc: You can only play this card if you have less than 7 <SHEEP>. Once this game, when you have 7 <SHEEP> on your farm, you immediately get 3 bonus <SCORE> and 2 <FOOD>.

name: Motivator
desc: On your first turn each round, if you have no unused farmyard spaces, you can place a person from your supply.

name: Loudmouth
desc: Each time you take at least 4 building resources or 4 animals from an accumulation space, you also get 1 <FOOD>.

name: Animal Tamer's Apprentice
desc: At the start of each round, you get 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> for each unoccupied wood/clay/stone room in your house.

name: Ox Skull
desc: During scoring, if you have no <CATTLE>, you get 3 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Margrave
desc: Once you live in a stone house, you get 2 <FOOD> each time any player renovates and, during scoring, 1 bonus <SCORE> for each wood house and clay house.

name: Garden Claw
desc: Place 1 <FOOD> on each remaining round space, up to three times the number of planted fields you have. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Fodder Planter
desc: In the breeding phase of each harvest, for each newborn animal you get, you can sow crops in exactly 1 field.

name: Elephantgrass Plant
desc: Immediately after each harvest, you can use this card to exchange exactly 1 <REED> for 1 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Clutterer
desc: During scoring, you get 1 bonus <SCORE> for each card played after this one that has "accumulation space(s)" in its text.

name: Lumberjack
desc: You immediately get 1 <WOOD>. Additionally, place 1 <WOOD> on each of the next round spaces, up to the number of fences you built. At the start of these rounds, you get the <WOOD>.

name: Inner Districts Director
desc: Each time you use the __Forest__ or __Clay Pit__ accumulation space, you can place 1 <STONE> from the general supply on the other space. If you do, you can immediately place another person.

name: Wool Blankets
desc: During scoring, if you live in a wooden/clay/stone house by then, you get 3/2/0 bonus <SCORE>.

name: Stork's Nest
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if you have more rooms than people, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to take a __Family Growth__ action.

name: Salter
desc: At any time, you can pay 1 <SHEEP>/<PIG>/<CATTLE> from your farm. If you do, place 1 <FOOD> on each of the next 3/5/7 round spaces. At the start of these rounds, you get the <FOOD>.

name: Livestock Expert
desc: If you play this card in round 11 or before, choose an animal type: you immediately get a number of animals of that type equal to the number you already have on your farm.

name: Sculpture
desc: You can only play this card if there are more complete rounds left to play than you have unused farmyard spaces.

name: Stall Holder
desc: Once per round, if you have 0/1/2/3/4 unfenced stables on your farm, you can exchange 2 <GRAIN> for 1 bonus <SCORE> and 1/2/3/4/5 <FOOD>.

name: Full Peasant
desc: Each time after you use the __Grain Utilization__ or __Fencing__ action space while the other is unoccupied, you can pay 1 <FOOD> to use the other space with the same person.

name: Beaver Colony
desc: From now on, one of your pastures with stable cannot hold animals. Each time you get <REED> from an action space, you get 1bonus <SCORE>.

name: Usufructuary
desc: When you play this card as your first occupation, you immediately get 1 <FOOD> for every other occupation in play (by any player), up to a maximum of 7 <FOOD>.

name: Luxurious Hostel
desc: During scoring, if you then have more stone rooms than people, you get 4 bonus <SCORE>. You can only use one card to get bonus points for your stone house.

name: Sequestrator
desc: Place 3 <REED> and 4 <CLAY> on this card. The next player to have 3 pastures/5 field tiles gets the 3 <REED>/4 <CLAY> (not retroactively).

name: Sugar Baker
desc: Each time after you use the __Grain Utilization__ action space, you can buy 1 bonus <SCORE> for 1 <FOOD>. Place the <FOOD> on the action space (for the next visitor).

name: Lifting Machine
desc: At the end of each round that does not end with a harvest, you can move 1 <VEGETABLE> from one of your fields to your supply. (This is not considered a field phase.)

name: Oven Site
desc: When you play this card, you get 2 <WOOD> and you can immediately build the __Clay Oven__ or __Stone Oven__ major improvement. Either way, it only costs you 1 <CLAY> and 1 <STONE>.

name: Forest Scientist
desc: In the returning home phase of each round, if there is no wood left on the game board, you get 1 <FOOD>from round 5 on, even 2 <FOOD>.
